title: anadama bread(yields 2 loaves)
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine corn meal with 1/2 cup water. Bring the remaining 1 1/2 cups of water to a boil and add to corn meal mixture.
Add shortening, molasses and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to corn meal mixture. Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about one hour.
Cut dough in half and shape.
Place in greased loaf pan, 9 x 5-inch.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about one hour.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 50 minutes.
Brush top with melted butter.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and garlic in oil, drain; add tomato sauce.
Add tomatoes and seasoning; simmer 30 minutes.
Cook noodles until tender, drain.
Arrange small amount of beef in greased dish.
Top with 1/2 of noodles, spread with 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/2 of Parmesan; top with 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers; top with remainder of beef mix and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese and butter; let stand at room temperature until soft.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix cheese and butter, then gradually add dry mixture.
Use a cookie press to make straws onto ungreased cookie sheets.
The bar and the star plates work best for this recipe.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: almond-coconut chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise and juice to make a good dipping consistency. Coat chicken with mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle with salt.
Coat with crumbs.
Place on rack and refrigerate until ready to cook. Melt some margarine in baking pan.
Place chicken pieces in pan. Pour some melted margarine over pieces (don't crowd in pan).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with toasted coconut and almonds.

title: scones
directions: Cut butter into first 5 ingredients.
Add egg mixed with buttermilk.
Add to first ingredients (fold in), handling as little as possible.
Pat out gently to 1/2 to 3/4 thickness.
Cut out scones 2 to 3-inch circles.
Bake in 400° oven 21 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: texas tidbits
directions: Over double boiler, melt the chocolate chips, then add and melt the butterscotch chips.
Stir together until smooth.
Stir in chopped nuts and then add chow mein noodles.
Completely mix together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate or freeze until serving.
Makes dozens!

title: apple dumplins
directions: Take biscuits and roll each one flat.
Place apples in each biscuit and pinch top and sides together.
Place each dumplin into a baking dish. Take sugar, melted butter, Sprite and cinnamon and boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour this liquid over each dumplin.
If you have additional chipped apples, you can add this around each dumplin. Bake at 350° until brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon nut brunch loaf
directions: Combine brown sugar, nuts, butter and cinnamon; set aside. Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Combine Carnation evaporated milk and water; stir in vinegar.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk mixture to creamed mixture; blend well after each addition.
Turn half the batter into greased and floured loaf pan(9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Top with brown sugar-nut mixture.
Spread with remaining batter.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crush the garlic.
Add it to the oil and let stand several hours.
Boil the egg just enough so that the egg white has turned white and the yolk is still runny (about 1 minute).
Immediately remove from boiling water, break it and beat slightly.
Cut the croutons and brown them in 1/4 cup of the garlic and oil.
Tear the romaine into bite-size pieces and place in salad bowl. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Break the egg over the salad and toss.

title: broccoli salad(number served: 6 to 8 people)
directions: Cut broccoli stalks to bite size pieces and mix all remaining ingredients with broccoli.
Mix together with dressing which contains the following ingredients:

title: green beans with bacon
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the first six ingredients. Cover and microwave on high for 6 minutes or until the beans are crisp-tender.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hermits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make 3 long strips in a 10 x 14-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Slice into 3-inch pieces. These are great!

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each addition.
Reduce speed.
Add flour and cream alternately.
Put in cold oven to bake at 275° to 300° for 1 hour without opening oven.
Then open oven and turn pan around and continue baking until done, about 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan or rack for a few minutes.
Then turn out to finish cooling.

title: tomato soup
directions: Do not dilute beef bouillon.
Combine tomato puree and bouillon in heavy pan.
Heat thoroughly, but do not allow to boil. Turn heat to low and simmer gently for 20 minutes.
(Longer simmering makes this soup even better.) Just before serving, squeeze in lime juice and stir.
Float the little green things on the surface.
Serve in large tureen or individual bowls.
Salt and pepper can be added at the table as desired.
Serves 6.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Mix hamburger meat in a little cold water, then mix other ingredients and cook on low heat, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Grind and mix with ground onions. Pour boiling water over this and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain. Mix vinegar, sugar and salt.
Let come to a boil.
Add other ingredients and boil 10 minutes.
Pack in sterile, hot jars. Makes about 9 pints.

title: fruit fluff pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup lemon juice with condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add well drained crushed pineapple, peaches and mandarin oranges.
Mix well.
Pour in crust and refrigerate overnight.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Roll into balls.
Dip in chocolate that has been melted. Store in refrigerator.

title: layered party dip
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in a serving bowl or dish.
Serve with large tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti and sauce
directions: Brown and drain hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add rest of ingredients.
Also add oregano (sparingly), bay leaf, garlic and salt to suit your taste.
Simmer several hours.
Freezes great.
(I use only tomato sauce.)
This makes enough sauce for at least 2 or 3 packages of spaghetti.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Make 1 gallon.
Keeps until used up if kept in an airtight container. Good to put in decorative containers to give as gifts.

title: old south poultry dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and white bread.
Pour over it the stock or water with butter.
Add onions (finely chopped) and eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Melt chocolate pieces and honey in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Add milk.
Pour in fondue pot and keep hot.
Serve with fresh fruit or pieces of angel food cake.
This is great as a hot fudge sauce also!

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Add 1 cup juice to pudding mix. Cook pudding, stirring constantly, until just thickened.
Cool. Fold in pineapple and oranges in pudding mixture.

title: three veggie cheese and pasta bake
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in margarine.
Stir in flour and cook, stirring constantly, but don't brown.
Stir in milk until blended and smooth.
Stir constantly until sauce thickens and boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salt and peppers.
Stir in mustard and all cheese, except 3 tablespoons. Toss cooked pasta with sauce.
Spoon into baking dish.
Arrange sliced tomatoes and squash over top.
Brush with some melted margarine and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove from oven, sprinkle with remaining cheese and let melt. Serves 6 to 8.

title: crazy pie
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9-inch pan or dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Then add 2 cups fruit (do not stir).
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cinnamon raisin french toast
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Dip bread slices in egg mixture until saturated.
Place bread on a hot greased griddle.
Fry bread until golden on both sides.
Serve immediately with butter and favorite topping.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large bowl, then add pecans. Shape into small balls and chill for several hours.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip each ball into mixture. Place on waxed paper.
Keep mixture hot while dipping.
Yields about 100 pieces.

title: beef paprika
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and place in crock-pot.
Add ketchup, spices and water.
Cook on low to medium heat, 8 to 12 hours. When ready, thicken with flour and water, if needed.

title: pasta and garbanzo bean soup
directions: Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium heat.
Add tomatoes, garlic and rosemary.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add 3 cups broth; stir to blend.
Puree remaining 1 cup broth and 1 cup garbanzo beans in blender.
Add to saucepan.
Add remaining whole garbanzo beans.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes. Add pasta; cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve, passing Parmesan separately.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: raspberry spinach salad
directions: In blender or with whisk, blend vinegar and jam.
Add salad oil in a thin stream.
Set aside.
Mix spinach, half of nuts, half of raspberries and all of dressing.
Top salad with remaining nuts, berries and kiwi fruit.
Mix lightly before serving.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Mix together sugar and baking powder.
Mix crushed crackers and nuts.
Gradually add sugar mixture, the vanilla and salt to beaten egg whites.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, cover with whipped cream.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, oil, Sweet 'N Low and eggs.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add fruits and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil spaghetti until tender and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the browned ground beef, sauce and 1 cup of the cheese.
Mix together and place the remaining 1 cup of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Best when cheese is browned for a couple of minutes under the broiler before removing pan from oven.
Let set a couple of minutes before cutting into squares.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix Velveeta, Ro-Tel and both cans of soup (undiluted) in a medium size saucepan or in a microwavable bowl.
Heat until cheese melts.
In baking dish or casserole dish, alternate layers of chicken, chips and cheese mixture, ending with chips on top.
Heat in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: red cider
directions: Heat ingredients until red hots dissolve.
Serve hot, minus cloves and cinnamon sticks.

title: popover chicken-mushroom sauce
directions: Brown the cut up chicken in the 2 tablespoons oil.
Beat eggs; add 1 1/2 cups milk and 1 tablespoon oil, then add flour and salt. Pour over chicken which is placed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan when browned.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with Easy Mushroom Sauce.

title: eggplant cheese fritters
directions: Mix egg yolks with crackers.
Beat egg whites.
Dip eggplant in cheese, then crackers, cheese again and last egg white.
Fry until golden brown.
Add water to tomato paste to make a light sauce. Simmer eggplant slices in tomato sauce or serve with sour cream or plain yogurt.

title: microwaved beefy onions
directions: Remove skin from onion.
Cut a V-shape out of the top of the onion.
Place butter, bouillon cube and a dash of salt in top of the onion.
Place on a microwave plate.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 5 minutes or until the onion begins to separate.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into balls.
Put in baking dish with lid.
Add 1 can golden mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked bean skillet
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, brown and drain ground beef and onion. Add remaining ingredients. Cook until bubbling, stirring occasionally. Serve hot, as a side dish. Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 12-inch baking dish, mix soups, water and rice until no lumps in soup.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate-cherry black forest cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: key lime pie
directions: Separate egg yolks from whites.
Set whites aside for meringue. In bowl, beat yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in condensed milk and lime peel.
Gradually add lime juices, beating at low speed just until combined.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in green food coloring, if desired.
Spoon lime mixture over filling.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool, cover and chill.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls into ungreased pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and Ranch dressing mix together.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Refrigerate and slice.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Stir together all dry ingredients. In separate bowl, beat butter 30 seconds.
Add sugar.
Beat.
Add eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to batter.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Can use Cream Cheese Icing.

title: no-fat oven fried fish
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Crush crackers; stir in dry mustard. Beat egg white with milk in a broad shallow bowl.
Spread cracker crumbs on a plate.
Dip fish fillets one at a time into egg mixture, then place in cracker crumbs and turn to coat all surfaces.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 425° for about 15 minutes until coating is crisp and fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve with lemon wedges if desired.

title: unusual fudge
directions: Melt butter and Velveeta cheese on low heat and pour into big mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients and pour into ungreased pan. This mixture comes out thick and a little hard to work with, but it turns out the right texture and is delicious.

title: orange-cranberry muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center and pour all wet ingredients into it.
Stir only until moistened. Stir in cranberries.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
These freeze great and make a tasty breakfast.
Thaw for 20 seconds in the microwave. Makes 12.

title: tomato and cucumber salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Peel, then slice cucumber.
Take cucumber slices and cut into fourths.
Cut tomato into bite size pieces.
Mix macaroni, cucumber and tomato together.
Add enough dressing to cover entire salad and mix. Chill prior to serving.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Saute half of chicken in 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet until tender; remove from skillet.
Repeat with 1 tablespoon oil and remaining chicken.
Saute peppers, onion and garlic in remaining 1 tablespoon oil until crisp-tender.
Add chicken to skillet; mix well.
Spread approximately 1 tablespoon cream cheese over each tortilla.
Place 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each tortilla; roll up.
Serve with salsa, if desired.

title: pineapple walnut cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in a bowl; mix.
Add eggs, pineapple and nuts.
Stir by hand.
Put in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or large cookie sheet with 1-inch rim.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° and 45 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not cool.
Frost immediately with frosting.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and refrigerate.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until edges are golden.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen cookies.

title: butterscotch cupcakes
directions: Add brown sugar to melted butter.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture.
Stir in pecan meats.
Fill well-greased muffin pan 2/3 full and place a pecan on top of each. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hot dog wrap(pig in a pillow)
directions: Mix together mix and water.
Form into ball.
Knead a few times and roll into 7 1/2 x 8-inch rectangle.
Cut into 10 rectangles and wrap hot dogs.
Bake in greased pan in a preheated oven at 450° for about 12 minutes or lightly browned.

title: appleless apple pie
directions: Bring to boil water, sugar and cream of tartar.
Drop in crackers.
Cook slow 10 minutes without stirring.
Pour into unbaked deep dish pie shells.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: pig licking good cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: cherry cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as directed. Spread in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, until fluffy.
Gradually add condensed milk, egg and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Pour evenly over brownie mix.
Bake 25 minutes longer or until set.
Cool.
Chill.
Stir 1/2 teaspoon almond extract into pie filling.
Spread on top.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: carne asada
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper; dredge in flour. Cook in small amount of grease; add chopped onion and cook slightly. Drain meat and onion. Add seasonings; stir and cook a short amount of time. Add Rotel and small amount of water. Serve hot.

title: oyster stew
directions: Slowly cook onion in butter until tender.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Heat until hot, but do not boil.
Add oysters with juice. Cook until edges of oysters begin to curl.
Spoon stew into warm soup bowls and serve with crackers.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: brandy slush
directions: Heat water and sugar until boiling.
Simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add juices and brandy and freeze.
To serve: Add 1/2 7-Up and 1/2 frozen mixture to glass.

title: mexican noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles; rinse and drain. Brown the ground beef and drain well. Add the taco seasoning mix. Stir in the tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes or until the liquid is almost gone. Gently mix the noodles with the cottage cheese, sour cream and green chilies. In a greased 2-quart casserole, layer the noodle mixture with the meat, then cheese. Repeat until used. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts and browns.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken in cold water and salt and pepper each piece. Mix Creole, flour, bread crumbs and seasoning salt in a plastic Ziploc bag.
Add a few wings at a time and shake the bag to coat evenly.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes, turning once at 20 to 25 minutes.

title: low-fat onion dip
directions: Mix skim milk and cottage cheese in blender.
Blend on high until smooth and creamy, approximately 3 minutes.
Stir in onion soup mix.
Chill one hour.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Mix ingredients
in
order and set aside to cool.
When cool and firm, shape into croquettes and dip in beaten egg and cracker crumbs,
then
egg
and
crumbs.
Fry in deep fat to a golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: jello gelatin jigglers
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in a bowl.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours. Cut into squares or cut with any cookie cutter.
Garnish as desired.
Cube remaining gelatin.
Keeps well in lunches and good finger snack.

title: shaker sugar pie
directions: Blend with a pastry cutter sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly.
Place in the pie shell.
Then pour over top of mixture whipping cream, vanilla and nutmeg (I use about 1/4 teaspoon of nutmeg).
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Very rich and good!

title: fresh fruit dip(low-fat)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cover.
Refrigerate while cutting up bananas, picked grapes, sliced apples, kiwi, strawberries, etc. Arrange on platter with dip in middle and serve with toothpicks.

title: herb mashed potatoes
directions: Simmer potatoes, salt and herbs in water until potatoes are soft. Drain potatoes and mash; add butter, milk and season to taste with salt and pepper. Serves 4.

title: gayle moore's sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; pack whole in quart jars.
Add all except sugar.
Finish filling jars with water and seal.
Process 5 minutes after water comes to a boil to seal lids.

title: kentucky angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve the soda in the buttermilk.
Mix yeast in warm water. Add buttermilk and yeast to flour mixture.
Mix until moist. Place in refrigerator.
Use as needed, or roll 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Dip in melted butter.
Bake at 400°.
Or you may let rise 1 hour before baking.

title: honey nut rolls
directions: Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Brush with melted butter. Mix brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Sprinkle over dough.
Pour honey onto the sugar and nut covered dough.
Roll up as for jelly roll. Oil muffin tins well.
Put 1 teaspoon brown sugar and 4 pecan halves in each ring.
Top with a 1 1/4-inch round of dough; cut end down.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise to double in size.
Bake 15 minutes or until light brown at 425°.
Invert while hot or the rolls will stick.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt the butter and stir in the flour.
Let cream sauce come to a boil and simmer for 1 minute.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Add cooked macaroni.
Pour this mixture into a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.
Make sure dish has been greased.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry apple spice drink
directions: Combine together and simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.
Makes 10 cups.

title: iron skillet meat loaf with gravy
directions: Do not preheat oven.
In a large mixing bowl, put hamburger. Add finely chopped onion, bread cut into cubes and 1/2 package of crackers.
Drain juice from tomatoes into a cup and save.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix ingredients together by squishing with "washed" hands.
Divide into 2 or 3 equal loaves and place in a 9-inch round iron skillet.
Pour juice around loaves and bake at 350° until done.
Remove loaves and place on high flame on top burner.
Add 2 tablespoons flour; mix well.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup milk. Stir until thickened.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients; stir until all is dissolved.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set. Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine and press first 3 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat well the next 4 ingredients (5 minutes).
When custard is smooth, spread over crust.
Slice bananas and press into custard.
Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Garnish with Cool Whip and nuts.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over and refrigerate.

title: seven minute chicken
directions: Combine soups, water and chicken in large frypan.
Stir in rice and bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 7 minutes.
Stir well, then sprinkle with onion rings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix flour, sugar, oleo and salt like pie crust.
Heat milk slightly; add beaten eggs, dry yeast and lukewarm water.
Add to flour mixture.
Let rise overnight.
Roll out like pie crust. Spread oleo, sugar and cinnamon on top.
Roll up and slice; let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in boiling water.
Stir until all marshmallows dissolve.
Stir Cool Whip and sherbet to soften. Add to Jell-O mixture.
Mix well.
Mold and refrigerate until firmly set.

title: super sausage bread
directions: Knead bread per package instructions.
Cook sausage and drain excess grease.
Roll bread flat and place sausage, cheese, etc. in center of bread.
Enclose sausage, etc. in bread by folding bread into loaf.
Smear top of loaf with one egg white for crust.
Cook at 325° until crust is brown.

title: diabetic lemon chiffon pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, lemon juice and water in saucepan.
Add salt and gelatin.
Cook and stir over medium heat, just to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 12 packets of Equal and lemon peel.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until partly set.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease oblong pan.

Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms. Pat dough in bottom and sides of pan with well floured hands. Cook meat with onions in skillet until done. Add oregano, salt, pepper and pizza sauce. Pour mixture in pan. Sprinkle with cheese, green pepper, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: baked potatoes elegante
directions: Bake potatoes in 375° oven for 70 to 80 minutes or until done. Cut slice from top of each.
Scoop out insides and mash.
Put empty potato skins aside for later.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, milk, butter, onion salt and pepper.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in chopped chives. Fill potato shells with mashed potatoes.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes or more until potatoes are heated through.
Serves 5.

title: banana cake
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until cake tests ready.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer until smooth. Pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake at 350 degrees for 50 - 60 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar after cooling.

title: pasta with a kick
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion. Cook for 5 minutes. Stir in garlic, red pepper flakes and salt. Cook 30 seconds. Add tomatoes and their liquid. Cook 15 minutes. Toss with pasta and parsley in a large serving bowl.
Makes 4 servings.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg.
Fold together crushed pineapple and whipped cream.
Place 1/2 wafers in bottom of dish.
Add mixed cream mixture; top with remaining crumbs.
Chill for 5 hours.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Brown crumbled sausage.
Crumble bread in 9 x 13 pan and put drained sausage over bread.
Layer cheese.
Beat eggs, soup and milk.
Add basil leaves and pour over bread, sausage and cheese. Drain mushrooms and put on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: mushroom-barley casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes and add mushrooms and barley.
Cook 10 minutes until barley starts to brown.
Stir in the stock, salt and pepper; transfer to a buttered casserole dish.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir in parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: old fashioned beef pot pie or yankee pot pie
directions: Cook meat in salt water until tender.
Remove meat from broth. Add onion to broth.
Bring to boiling point and add alternate layers of cubed potatoes and squares of dough.
Make sure your dough has been rolled out very thin.
To make pot pie dough, beat egg and add milk and flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out thin in squares.
Keep broth boiling while adding dough in order to keep them from packing together.
Cover; cook on low for about 20 minutes.
Add more water if needed.
This is delicious with buttered bread.

title: peach buttermilk salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in saucepan and heat to dissolve. Bring to a boil; cool thoroughly.
Add buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Make cake as package label directs.
Turn into pan.
Bake. Cool completely.

title: hot tamales
directions: Mix onions, water and cumin in blender.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Take one tablespoon of mixture and roll until it is 3 inches long.
Roll in masa meal until evenly coated, then wrap tamales in paper which has been soaked in water.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix jello like directions say.
Grate carrots and add pineapple.
Use juice from pineapple as part of cold water from jello.

title: grandma's good white cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except flour.
Add enough flour to the mixture to be able to roll the dough out with a rolling pin.
Sprinkle some flour out on the countertop to prevent sticking.
Roll the dough out.
Using a cookie cutter, cut shapes in the dough.
Bake dough at 325°.
Bake about 10 minutes or until dough springs back when lightly touched.
Frost and enjoy.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Take box of pudding and 1 cup pineapple juice; cook and boil until transparent.
Cool.
Mix in fruit.
Cool.
Serves about 12.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut asparagus in 1-inch pieces.
Cook until tender; drain.
Make a sauce of butter, flour, seasonings and 1 cup soft bread crumbs.
Put a layer of asparagus in bottom of 1-quart, buttered casserole.
Add sauce and half of hard-boiled eggs.
Repeat with additional layer.
Sprinkle with dried, buttered crumbs, mixed with the cheese.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices.
Precook in boiling salted water.
Remove from heat and drain.
Layer potatoes, bacon and green onion in greased casserole dish.
Set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt, pepper and celery seed and cook, stirring, for about 2 minutes.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly and cook until sauce is thick.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Pour sauce evenly over potatoes and cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 or 20 minutes more.

title: brown caramel candy
directions: Take 1 1/2 cups of sugar and brown while 3 cups sugar, milk and butter come to a boil in another container.
Pour browned sugar in with this and cook until soft ball forms in water.
Beat until creamy; add nuts and drop on wax paper.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together except pecans.
Stir well.
Pour into large bowl and top with nuts, then chill.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 3 layers.
Use 9-inch pans.

title: omelet sandwich
directions: Place 6 buttered slices of bread with buttered side down in casserole dish.
Top each slice with chopped ham and cheese.
Top with remaining bread.
Beat eggs with milk and dry mustard.
Pour over all.
Top with cornflakes mixed with melted butter. Refrigerate overnight or let stand 4 hours.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until topping is crispy brown.
(Topping may be added before baking, instead of being added before refrigerator.) Serves 6.

title: apple dip
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over low heat (or on low in microwave) until smooth and melted.
Core apples and slice.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Dip slices of apple into the apple dip.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar and stir into margarine. Add eggs and mix again, slightly beating. Stir in buttermilk. Add vanilla and stir again. Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until a knife blade inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: dannon apple spice cake
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly combine the flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice, salt and cloves. Add applesauce, yogurt, egg substitute and oil.
Blend well, using spoon. Stir in raisins. Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt or 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Loosen cake from sides of pan with knife.
Invert onto plate.
Cover loosely with foil or wax paper.
Cool completely. Slice and serve with Quick Yogurt Glaze.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer the following:
Layer the bean dip.
Layer the avocados for second layer.
Blend the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix for the third layer.
Mix together the remaining ingredients for fourth layer.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Beat cream cheese until soft.
Add flavoring.
Gradually add sugar; knead until consistency of pie dough.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Roll into small balls.
Dip one side of ball in powdered sugar and press that side into rubber mold.
Press out onto waxed paper to dry.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown the ground beef; pour off the fat.
Add the spaghetti sauce mix, water and tomato paste.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Keep hot in 400° oven.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Sift flour 4 times.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour a little at a time.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thick and cut into 1-inch squares.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab muffins
directions: Melt butter; add spices, then cheese, then crab meat.
Blend well.
Top English muffins.
Bake at 350° until bubbles on top. Cut into quarters.
Can be frozen.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except coconut in large
mixer bowl. Beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour into 2 prepared layer cake pans (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not underbake.
Cool well.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together and layer on top of mixture in pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: meat pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and season with remaining ingredients.
Bring to simmer and add 1 tablespoon cornstarch dissolved in 1 tablespoon water.
Stir until thickened.
Place filling in 2 (9-inch) pie crusts; cover with top crust and brush with cream or rich milk.
Crimp edges and pierce top crust in several places.
Bake in preheated 425° for 20 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and continue to bake until golden brown.
Freezes well.
Serve with a green salad.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain oil.
Add taco seasoning mix, salsa and mushroom soup.
Mix all together.
Put Velveeta cheese on top and melt.
Eat dip with nachos.

title: spiced tea
directions: Store in an airtight container.

title: bleu cheese dip
directions: Mix together or use blender.

title: tuna dip
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until cheese is melted.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup of cold water and add to soup and let set until cool.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well and mold.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, then add eggs.
Mush bananas and add to mixture.
Stir 1 teaspoon baking soda into sour milk and then add to mixture.
Then add flour and nuts.
Stir well.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: dressed-up meatballs
directions: Place meatballs in a 3 qt. microwave-safe dish.
Top with onion, carrots, green pepper, and garlic.
Combine sauces and pour over meatballs.
Cover and microwave on high for 8-10 minutes stirring twice or until vegetables are tender and meatballs are heated through.
Serve over hot rice.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with syrup, coconut and eggs in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Bring butter, sugar and milk to a boil in a small saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat. Stir in 1 1/2 cups coconut.
Pour over hot cake.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, salt, pepper, onion, sour cream and cheese. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix crushed cornflakes and margarine; top the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix together the meat, rice, egg, onion, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Arrange green pepper halves in an 11 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Fill peppers with meat mixture.
Mix together the remaining tomato sauce, water and sugar; pour over green peppers.
Cover with tight fitting lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 20 to 25 minutes, or until meat is no longer pink and green peppers are tender.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry filling.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with real whipped cream.

title: dipping batter for tempura
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until smooth.
Can be prepared ahead and kept in the refrigerator.
If batter thickens, add 1 tablespoon milk.
Dip sliced vegetables or cooked chicken, shrimp, or beef into batter.
Fry in oil heated to 375°.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp well. Drain and pat dry. Sprinkle with a little salt. In a large, shallow pan, melt butter. Add Italian seasoning and garlic. Place shrimp in single layer in pan. Sprinkle with black pepper. Turn oven to broil and broil shrimp for 5 to 7 minutes or until they turn pink. Stir and turn over all shrimp. Broil on this side for 5 to 7 minutes or until pink. Serve immediately. Good served with hot French bread.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, beating after each addition until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Add half of flour and milk.
Continue beating; add flavor and balance of flour.
Beat at least 3 minutes more.
Pour in layer cake pan.
Ice as desired.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Melt oleo in 10-inch skillet.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add cubed chicken, onion, peas and carrots.
Simmer until hot.
Pour in baking dish.
Arrange biscuits over top of chicken mixture. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375° until biscuits are browned.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Cook beef, onions and chili sauce.
Add spices.
Divide into 8 parts.
Spread on buns.
Place 2 strips of cheese on mixture. Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ham.

title: quick peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine cake mix, peanut butter and butter in large bowl.
Mix at low speed with electric mixer until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet and remove to rack.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops, pepper, onion and celery.
Add canned tomatoes and sauce along with rice and enough water to cook the rice.
Cover and simmer until rice is done.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add the pineapple.
The rings can be laid on top or chopped up and stirred in rice.

title: carnation pumpkin pie
directions: *For spices, you may use 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.

title: easy chicken divan(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook broccoli as package directs. Drain well. Arrange stalks in greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Place chicken on top of broccoli. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and most of cheese. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "intermezzo" jello mold
directions: Make Jell-O using 1/2 the required water.
Mix all ingredients except sour cream into Jell-O.
Pour 1/3 of mixture into bowl used for serving.
Refrigerate until it hardens (leave the remaining Jell-O mixture on counter).
When refrigerated, mixture hardens. Spread sour cream over Jell-O.
Top with the remaining 2/3 Jell-O mixture.
Chill until hardened.

title: baked camembert with hazelnut crust(serves 8 to 10)
directions: In a shallow dish, coat the Camembert well on all sides with the egg.
In another shallow dish, combine the bread crumbs and hazelnuts.
Coat the Camembert well on all sides with the mixture, patting the mixture on to help it adhere and chill it on a plate, covered, for 1 hour.
On a baking sheet, bake the Camembert rindless side up in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Transfer Camembert to a platter and serve hot with the apple slices and brioche.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked cabbage puff
directions: Cover cabbage with cold water and heat to boiling.
Drain well.
In buttered, shallow 2-quart baking dish, arrange cabbage, crumbs and cheese in layers, making 2 layers of each.
Beat eggs with salt, mustard and pepper.
Add milk and pimiento and mix well.
Pour over cabbage, pressing mixture down into the liquid. Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 45 minutes, until puffed and set in center of dish.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: spiced cranberry and orange relish
directions: In a small saucepan, bring the sugar and water to a boil over moderately low heat.
Once the sugar has dissolved, simmer the syrup for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into a ball.
Chill and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Hold Jell-O and 1/2 of Cool Whip to the side.
Mix all other ingredients.
Sprinkle powdered Jell-O onto fruit salad.
Top with Cool Whip as served.

title: italian ricotta cake
directions: Follow directions on box for cake mix.
Mix all ingredients of cake mix and set aside.
In another bowl, blend by hand the Ricotta, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Pour cake mix into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Pour Ricotta mixture on top of cake mix and smooth it out to the edges of the pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°; test with toothpick.
Cake will be moist, but will harden up after cooling.
Cool 15 minutes, then remove from pan.
After cake has cooled, follow directions on box for pudding mix.
Let pudding get firm by putting in refrigerator for a few minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip into pudding, then spread on cake for icing.
Bon appetite.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: Mix throughly 1/4 cup of the soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape into 4 to 6 patties.

title: butternut squash and roasted pepper soup
directions: Add butter, squash, peppers and sugar to a soup pan.
To roast peppers; blister skin over open flame or roast in oven.
Scrape off the skin and seed.
Saute ingredients in pan on low flame for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add thyme and chicken stock.
Simmer for 1 hour or until squash has broken down and soup has a smooth texture. Add roux to thicken, then add heavy cream.
Season to taste.

title: turkey rolls
directions: Fix stuffing according to directions on the box.
Roll turkey slice up with 2 tablespoons stuffing inside.
Place rolls in small casserole dish with any remaining stuffing on the side.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Melt oleo in pan (take off stove).
Add sour cream, mixing well.
Add sugar and eggs.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add flour and salt to yeast.
Mix with other ingredients.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Divide in 3 balls.
Roll out to 10-inch circles. Spread with butter.
Cut into 12 wedges (each ball).
Roll large end first.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix together; sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours or until rice is soft.

title: marshmallow crispy treats
directions: Melt margarine over low heat. Add marshmallows, stir until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in cereal until well coated. Press into greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: reese squares
directions: Mix together everything except chocolate chips and press in dish.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: garden vegetable stew
directions: Spread the tomatoes over the bottom of a deep pan or a 3-quart casserole which can go to the table.
Top the tomatoes with onion and garlic, then layer with zucchini, then romaine.
Top romaine with peas and sprinkle half of the parsley and oil over the mixture.
Add the limas and sprinkle remaining parsley on top. Sprinkle remaining olive oil over everything.

title: swedish sausage ring
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a 9-inch ring mold. Mix ingredients
well
and
pack into mold.
Bake 20 minutes. Take from oven and pour off excess fat.	Bake 20 minutes more. Turn onto
a
heated
platter and fill with scrambled eggs if desired.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Blend eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in sheet pan 15-20 minutes at 350°.

title: dorothy tucker's macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Chop bell pepper, onion and cucumber. Blend mayonnaise and vinegar; add more to taste.
Mix macaroni, vegetables and celery seed.
Pour mayonnaise and vinegar mixture over.
Blend well.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan in the following order: lettuce, celery, peas, pepper and onion. Spread salad dressing over top and top with shredded cheese. Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours. Keeps well for 3 to 4 days.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and mushrooms; drain. Put in 8 x 8-inch dish. Top with pizza sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Mix baking mix, eggs and milk. Mix well. Pour on top of meat mixture. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top looks completely cooked.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a cake pan or glass dish.
Let chill until firm.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 3 (1 pound) coffee cans or can be baked in loaf pan.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and warm water and set aside.
Sift flour with dry ingredients; gradually add liquids, adding oil last.
Make biscuits and let stand 30 minutes before baking in 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Spread in glass dish.
Put in fridge until cold.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Crust Ritz crackers; add 1 stick melted butter.
Set aside.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1/2 cup soup, beef, onion, crumbs and egg.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, firmly shape mixture into an 8 x 4-inch loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove meat loaf from oven. Pour off fat.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine salmon, eggs, meal and flour together.
Form into patties.
Fry in cooking oil (only) for 5 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp spread or dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Add shrimp last.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: confetti vegetable rice
directions: Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add next 4 ingredients and saute 4 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Set aside. Drain tomatoes, reserving tomatoes and liquid separately.
Combine chicken broth and reserved liquid.
Add tomato wedges and broth mixture to saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and cilantro. Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lasting bubbles
directions: This diet is designed to help you cope with the stress that builds up during the day.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Place in container with cover. Chill to blend flavors.
Serve with assorted crackers, potato chips and crisp vegetables.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in roaster or large baking pan.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour over spareribs.
Cover securely and cook in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and bake for 30 more minutes, basting occasionally.

title: honey wings
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken wings.
Marinate 4 hours or overnight.
Place chicken wings on cookie sheet.
Bake until wings are sticky, about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy nut or poppy seed rolls(4 rolls)
directions: Put yeast in bowl; add sugar, salt and water and let set. Make a well in the center and drop in egg yolk and yeast mixture. Using hands, mix thoroughly until dough leaves the sides of the bowl.
Place dough on lightly floured board and cut in 4 pieces. Let rest while you make your filling.
Roll out dough thin, about 15-inch circle; spread with filling and roll up as for jelly roll. Place on lightly greased pans (10 x 15-inch for two).
Brush tops with beaten egg whites and let rise for 25 minutes.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy salsa
directions: Cut ends off peppers, cut in half lengthwise.
Place in pan with water to cover; cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in food processor or blender with minced garlic, chop.
Add tomatoes and dash of salt.
Process to desired consistency.
More or less peppers can be used to adjust heat to taste.
Store in jar in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups. Beat egg; stir in buttermilk, brown sugar and shortening.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffins 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Bring jello and pineapple almost to a boil.
Cool and add buttermilk.
Then whip in the Cool Whip.

title: raisin cake
directions: In a large saucepan boil raisins and water for 10 minutes. Then add butter or oil.
Let mixture cool.
Add flour, soda, salt, sugar and spices into cooled mixture in pan and mix.
Add nuts if you like.

title: sausage and beans
directions: Thinly slice onions.
Saute onions, green peppers and garlic in olive oil.
Transfer to a large pot and set aside.

title: corned beef
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Let cool and pour over raw meat (meat must be in a crock, glass or stainless steel container).
Keep in refrigerator or cool area.
Marinate in this solution for 6 days or 2 days per pound of meat.
After this amount of time, jab meat with a fork or sharp object and cover meat with meat tenderizer, then slice 2 pieces of garlic thin and cover meat with the slices and let set for 1 hour.
After this time, boil the meat in this same solution.
Boil slowly until meat is thoroughly cooked. After refrigerating meat, it will be ready to eat.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine. Beat 2 minutes. Cover and let set at room temperature 4 days. Stir down daily.

title: fruit rolls
directions: Put mashed up vanilla wafers in bowl.
Stir in Eagle Brand, red and green cherries and pecans.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and roll in coconut.
Makes a bunch.

title: night before french toast
directions: Arrange bread in single layer in baking dish.
In medium bowl with eggbeater, beat eggs with milk, orange juice, sugar, vanilla and salt until blended.
Pour over bread.
Turn slices to coat evenly.
Refrigerate.
Cover overnight.
Fry in butter and enjoy. Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread in casserole dish, then meat, then cheese.
Combine milk and eggs.
Pour over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best slaw
directions: Chop or shred fine the cabbages, onion and green pepper; set aside.
In saucepan, combine other ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight or minimum 12 hours. Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Beat margarine,
sugars
and
egg
yolks together.
Mix soda with
buttermilk
and
add	alternately
with flour.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Beat
egg whites stiff and blend in last. Bake in greased and
floured
tube	pan at 350° for 2 hours or until toothpick stuck
in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan a few minutes, then turn out to finish cooling.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. In a large mixer bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat on high speed 3 minutes.

title: tuna sauce for pasta
directions: Add parsley to tuna.
Set aside.
In skillet, add anchovies with oil and fry for a few minutes.
Add chopped tomatoes and simmer.
When most of liquid is absorbed, add tuna mixture, salt and pepper and cook 5 more minutes.
Pour over hot cooked, drained pasta.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Equal parts peanut butter and sugar.
Add milk by tablespoon just until moistened.
Melt chocolate chips and Crisco.
Roll peanut butter mixture into balls and place onto waxed paper.
Dip into chocolate and return to waxed paper to chill.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Slice strawberries or leave whole.
Mix strawberry glaze with strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell that has been cooled.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: quick veggie dip
directions: Mix well; refrigerate for at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken tender and remove bones and skin. Lay bite size pieces of chicken in bottom of casserole. Blend soups and sour cream and spread over chicken. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, approximately 20 minutes.

title: impossible egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar and flour good with eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 10-inch greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes its own crust.
It's better served warm.

title: scripture cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with unsalted shortening.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
In the large bowl of an electric mixer, beat butter at medium speed until creamy.
Add sugar 1/3 cup at a time, beating well after each addition and scraping the sides of the bowl often.
Reduce speed to low, mix in honey and then add sifted dry ingredients 1/3 cup at a time, alternating with the milk.
Stir in figs and almonds.
Pour batter in prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Turn cake on wire rack and cool.

title: orange butter
directions: Cream all together.
Use as a spread for hot rolls, breads, etc.
Can be stored indefinitely in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Pound breast halves slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken on high for 3 or 4 minutes on each side.
(Take chicken out.)
Add onion, lime juice, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Add broth, butter and oil, whisking constantly.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Roll steak in this flour mixture. Fry in 1/2 cup oil on medium-high until medium brown. Remove steak and set aside. Saute onions in the excess oil. Remove and set aside with steak. Add enough flour to drippings to make a paste. Stir constantly on medium-high heat. Add 1/2 cup milk and about 1 1/2 cups water. Cook until thick. Pour gravy in crock-pot with steak and cook on high about 4 hours.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, saving about 1/4 of the juice.
Add vinegar to equal the amount of juice and 1/4 cup sugar. Pour over beets.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add walnuts and apples; mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Test to see if done by pressing finger on top of cake and if it springs back, it is done.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Add celery, apples (sprinkled with lemon juice), onion and grapes to the cooked chicken pieces.
Blend the curry powder, mayonnaise and light cream.
Add almonds.
Mix all of this with chicken mixture.
Chill.
Serves 6 in tomato cups.

title: diabetic cake(no sugar)
directions: Cook raisins in the 2 cups of water until all water is gone; let cool.
Add applesauce, eggs, Sweet 'N Low and oil.
Mix well. Sift dry ingredients together and add to applesauce mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt or other pan at 350° for 15 minutes or until cake is done.
You can add 1/2 cup chopped nuts if you like.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Add sugar and flour to butter.
Blend well.
Add eggs, flavoring and buttermilk.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until center is almost firm.

title: banana breakfast shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and turn to high speed.
Blend for 45 seconds, or until creamy and smooth.
To serve, pour into tall glass.
Yield:
1 shake.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and vanilla.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients, mix with creamed mixture.
Form into tiny balls with hands, and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with the back of a fork to make a crisscross on each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until brown.

title: chocolate mint cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, melted oleo, eggs and Hershey's chocolate syrup.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in large, sided cookie sheet (17 x 11-inch), greased and floured.
Cool this layer.
Can put in refrigerator.

title: mandelbroit(almond cakes)
directions: Combine eggs and shortening; beat well.
Gradually add sugar. Mix well.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add gradually to mixture.
Stir in nuts and flavorings.
Lightly grease hands and shape into six 4-inch loaves.
Lay on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Slice loaves.
Place cut side down on cookie sheet.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk; stir until thick.
Add cream cheese and margarine; mix well, then add confectioners sugar and Cool Whip. Mix well, then set aside.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cake and topping
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Cream oleo and sugars.
Blend in eggs.
Add oatmeal mixture.
Add flour, cinnamon and soda.

title: shortcake
directions: Beat sugar, butter and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend well and pour into 18 cupcake tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat the eggs, oil and sugar.
Add the grated squash.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, baking powder, ginger, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts; stir into batter. Bake in greased loaf pans (2) at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients, except nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Stir well. Pour into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans and cool on racks.
Great with cream cheese.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare the rice according to instructions on package; set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Combine sauce, rice, chicken, mushrooms, green pepper and pimento.
Pour into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Refrigerate several hours. Remove from refrigerator; let stand 30 minutes.
Remove cover; bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add sugar. Boil 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in instant coffee. Remove from heat. Add alcohol. Stir and bottle.

title: ham loaf
directions: *Humberts meats will grind this.

title: cherry wafer tarts
directions: Mix cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla; cream well.
Place 1 wafer in miniature muffin pan lined with miniature cupcake liners.
Place mixture on top of wafer 3/4 full.
Put in oven for 12 minutes at 375°.
Let cool slightly.
Place cherry pie filling on top.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes.
Add dry ingredients; mix 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and pecans; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Add 10 ice cubes and blend again.

title: chili(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes until meat is almost cooked.
Pour off fat.
Break up meat into smaller pieces.
Stir in raw vegetables. Microwave 4 to 5 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Microwave 5 minutes at High. Remove cover and stir.
Microwave, uncovered, at 50% power (medium) for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring at least once.
Serves 2 quarts.

title: vegetable lasagna(less calories)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
In large bowl, combine spinach, zucchini, cottage and Parmesan cheese, mushrooms, carrots, onions and eggs; stir to mix well. Set aside.
In prepared pan, spread tomato sauce to cover bottom of pan; next place lasagna noodles over sauce, then spread half of the vegetable mixture over noodles.
Repeat layering, ending with sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Uncover and top mixture with Mozzarella cheese; bake uncovered for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting. Serves 6.

title: harold's casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Put in a large crock-pot.
Add 1 cup water.
Slice carrots and potatoes.
Put in frozen vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are done.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Add vanilla, crushed pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 (9-inch) round cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely before frosting.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix and pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with more crumbs and drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until bubbly and brown.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Let cucumbers and onions soak in salt and water for 3 hours or overnight.
Pour off brine, but don't rinse.
Add rest of ingredients in a large pan; bring to boil.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes and can hot.

title: caramel sauce(for puddings)
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar, then cornstarch which has been dissolved in the water. Bring slowly to the boiling point, stirring until blended. Remove from heat. Add vanilla (brandy or rum may be substituted).
Serve warm sauce over pudding.

title: mom's cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Beat all the ingredients for 8 minutes and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or a Bundt pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Swirl.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. It is good without icing or use 1 cup powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon butter flavoring and 2 tablespoons milk for the icing.

title: chili-rice peppers
directions: Remove seed from peppers; steam about 10 minutes.
Cook onion in oil until tender and combine with chili and rice.
Fill peppers with mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Place in baking dish with water in bottom.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix 2 packages Kool-Aid with 2 quarts water and 2 cups sugar. Freeze in ice cubes.
Mix 1 package Kool-Aid with 2 quarts water and 1 cup sugar. Add ginger ale and pineapple juice. Add ice cubes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach in microwave until thawed; drain.
Mix all the ingredients together and chill.
Form balls (use approximately 1 tablespoon).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bride's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to mixture. Blend lightly.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thickness and cut out. Dough may be stored in refrigerator or cut out and frozen.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk and flavoring.
Remove beater and fold in coconut.
Bake in a greased and floured angel cake pan (tube pan) for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: In small bowl, combine chicken, cheese, onions, chilies, salsa and garlic salt.
Carefully fold in avocado.
Divide mixture evenly among tortillas.
Carefully fold in sides of tortillas, making sure to enclose all of the filling.
Secure on ends with wooden toothpicks.
Deep fat fry at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with sour cream and salsa.
Makes 8 servings.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for 1 minute. Pour into greased and floured pie pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 2 large or 3 small pans.

title: bird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients with enough water or skim milk to make a thick batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Put in mesh bag and hang from tree.

title: broccoli-beef pie
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes or until tender.
Brown meat; drain drippings.
Stir in mushrooms, 1 1/2 cups of cheese and onion. Set aside.

title: fruit pie
directions: Stir cornstarch into cold water until thoroughly dissolved. Add this to fruit and concentrated apple juice and stir over medium heat until thick.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: *Can be made from scratch or use Cheddar cheese soup; season with oregano.

title: sesame-ginger chicken
directions: Combine the first four ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Place the chicken between two sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Coat the grill rack with cooking spray; place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Place the chicken on the rack and cook four minutes on each side, basting frequently with the soy sauce mixture.
Transfer the chicken to a serving platter; garnish with the green onions, if desired.
Serves four.

title: melt in your mouth muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Grease muffin cups.
Mix together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Beat egg, but not too much.
Add milk and melted fat to egg.
Pour egg mixture into bowl with flour.
Stir until all ingredients are thoroughly blended.
Fill muffin cups half full.

title: lemony light cooler(makes 7 cups)
directions: In pitcher, combine juice, sugar and ReaLemon.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Chill juice before serving.
Add club soda, fruit and ice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 300°.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until pie is not shaky in center.
Delicious.

title: tess's nice breath biscuits(for dogs)
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, mint and parsley in large bowl.
Add oil and water; mix thoroughly.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness of floured surface and cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let biscuits dry in oven several hours.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: cream goddess dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill thoroughly.
Makes 2 cups dressing.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips and walnuts.
Spread in greased foil-lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan.
Lift out of pan.
Cut into squares or shapes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: play clay
directions: Boil together 3/4 cup water and salt.
Add mixture of cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Stir and remove from stove.
Add coloring.
When cool, work with your hands until smooth.
Store in covered container.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix rhubarb and pineapple together.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add to mixture; put into pie shell.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Dot on top of pie before putting on top pie crust.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Put pineapple in to drain while cutting up rhubarb.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Press into a loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour; drain fat.
Let stand 5 minutes, then serve.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add the egg, fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Stir gently; do not beat.
Bake in a 2 x 5 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, carrot and onion and steam until tender.
Drain. Mix the following:
margarine, cornbread, chicken soup, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Mix sauce mixture with vegetables and place in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and clear. Quickly stir in egg yolks.
Boil 1 minute more.
Remove from heat. Stir in 1/3 cup of lemon juice, salt and butter.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese and condensed milk until smooth.
Add pudding mix and remaining 1/3 cup lemon juice.
Fold into cooled pudding.
Divide in pie shells.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and lemon slices.
Enjoy!

title: corn-cheese casserole
directions: Soak crumbs in milk.
Add other ingredients, except paprika and some of the cheese, and mix together.
Also keep butter aside while mixing other ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole. Sprinkle top with cheese and paprika.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until center sets.
Remove cover long enough to lightly brown top.

title: venison roast
directions: Put in pan.
Sprinkle soup mix on roast .
Spoon mushroom soup over roast.
Add just enough water to rinse out the can.
Cover with foil and bake in a slow oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons oleo until soft.
Stir in flour; add water.
Cook over low heat until thickened and comes to a boil.
Blend in cheese.
Combine cheese sauce and broccoli; add eggs and mix gently.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with crushed crackers.
Dot with remaining oleo.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Rinse in cold water.
While macaroni is cooking, in medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour, bouillon and mustard.
Gradually stir in milk until mixture thickens slightly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Turn into 8 x 8-inch pan or shallow baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: impossible ham 'n swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches. Sprinkle ham, cheese and onions in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream
together all ingredients but Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Crush beer nuts and sprinkle on top.
Freeze.

title: frozen bread sticky buns
directions: Let bread thaw several hours, not raised.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Tear one loaf in small pieces and lay in bottom of pan.
Melt butter. Add brown sugar, pudding and milk.
Pour over and sprinkle with cinnamon, nuts and raisins.
Tear the second loaf on top.
Let raise and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When they're done, flip pan over and let them fall out.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well, then add eggs.
Bake at 325° approximately 40 minutes until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Brown chicken breasts until done.
In glass dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, melt butter in microwave.
Add chopped onion and broccoli to butter mixture.
Simmer in butter for 30 seconds.
Add rice, milk and cream of chicken soup.
Lay chicken breasts on top of mixture.
Scatter broccoli through dish.
Add Velveeta cheese on top and cook in microwave for 5 minutes on Medium power or until rice is done.

title: whiskey cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, eggs and butter in a large mixing bowl.
Then add rest of the ingredients in the order given.

title: hamburger barley soup
directions: Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, then remove bay leaves.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; pour sugar over them and let sit.
Dissolve Jell-O in water; let cool until it begins to set, then add the cranberries, pineapple, cherry and nuts.
Let set until firm.

title: juliann's fat-free, hearty mushroom-barley soup
directions: In a large covered saucepot, bring broth and barley to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms; simmer until mushrooms are tender, about 15 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: mother's spice cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Bake in 350° oven.
May bake in a Bundt pan.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a 5-quart Dutch oven; bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 238°, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9-inch pans.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: fairy pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add next 4 ingredients, then crackers and mix well.
Bake in slow oven (300° to 325°) for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with ice cream or
Cool Whip.

title: greek cheese and spinach squares
directions: Beat eggs, whole wheat flour, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and salt in large bowl until smooth.
Add fresh spinach.

title: crunchy bread sticks
directions: Open and separate biscuits.
Cut each biscuit in half.
Roll each half in hands until 5 inches long.
Dip in evaporated milk, then roll in cheese.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pecan divinity roll
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until syrup is hard when dropped on water (hard crack stage).
While syrup is cooking, beat egg whites until very stiff.
When syrup has reached hard crack stage, pour slowly over egg whites.
Add vanilla, continue beating until very stiff and cool enough to handle.
Form into rolls.

title: ga ga's chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Use large pot.
Cover cut up chicken and onion with water and cook until tender.
Remove chicken and remove from bone when cooled.
Add meat back into broth and simmer.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
With flour in large bowl, add broth to flour slowly until you can mix together with hands to form a ball (should not be sticky).
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 3-inch pieces and drop into simmering broth.
Simmer until tender.
You may add lima beans or potatoes to this recipe also.
Broth will thicken as you simmer.

title: duchess potatoes
directions: To mashed potatoes, add 1 tablespoon butter or margarine, the beaten egg yolk and salt and pepper to taste; mix well.
Push mounds of potato mixture from large spoon onto greased baking sheet.
Drizzle with 1 tablespoon melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Puree the strawberries in blender. Combine eggs and oil in small bowl. Whisk thoroughly.
Sift remaining ingredients into large bowl.
Make well in center.
Pour in eggs and puree and blend well.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until tester comes out clean. Serve with strawberry butter, if desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water together and let cool.
Add Port wine, pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts; refrigerate until set.
Whip cream cheese, confectioners sugar and sour cream until well blended.
Spread topping evenly over congealed salad and refrigerate until time to serve.
Cut into squares before serving.

title: simply delicious pork chops
directions: Arrange chops in single layer in baking dish.
In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread half of mixture over chops.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Turn chops and spread with remaining mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes more.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onion and beef, drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except tortillas and cheese).
Alternate layer of meat mixture and tortillas in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet-sour-mustard
directions: Mix in jar -
1/2 cup dry mustard and 1/2 cup vinegar.
Let stand over night.
In a sauce pan, beat 1 egg - stir in 1/4 cup sugar, pinch of salt and above mustard mixture. Cook over low heat stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Cool.
Blend in 1 cup mayonnaise (very good makes Baloney taste like ham). Refrigerate.

title: dolores' caramel corn
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together for 5 minutes; remove from stove.
Add the vanilla, baking soda and salt.
This will foam up.
Blend and pour over the popcorn.
Put the popcorn in a roasting pan; pour liquid over the popcorn.
Place in a 250° oven; cook for 15 minutes.
Stir every 3 to 5 minutes.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla. Beat until smooth and creamy in texture, adding more milk a drop at a time if necessary.
Store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks, beating again before using.
Makes 3 cups of stiff icing for decorating.
Add 2 teaspoons of milk per cup of icing to thin it for icing cakes.
You can use stiff icing to make flowers, medium stiff icing to make borders, and thin icing to make writing and leaves.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and chill!

title: pizza sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes and garlic together until soft, then strain by putting through a vegetable grinder.
Put onions and peppers through food chopper, then put in skillet with oil, oregano and basil; cook 1/2 hour.
Then cook all together.
Add sugar and salt.
Cook this all for 1 hour.
Put in clean jars and seal. This is very good to use with your tomato paste for spaghetti.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and combine with tuna, vegetables and salt. Blend soup and milk and add cheese, stirring until cheese melts. Add mayonnaise.
Add to noodle mixture and bake in 2 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
