May be topped with slivered almonds or crushed potato chips.

title: christmas cookies
directions: *I use substitute eggs, also.
I think the cookies are too rich when iced.

title: crunchy cookies
directions: Mix the peanut butter and butterscotch chips in top of double boiler.
Melt partially; cool and mix in corn flakes.
Drop onto a cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator until cold.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces and dredge in mixture of flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Hammer meat and brown in a large skillet.
Add the tomatoes and layer onion, carrots and green pepper over meat.
Sprinkle the brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce over the top of the vegetables. Cover tightly, lower temperature to low-medium and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: clam bake
directions: Wash and
scrub
clams	until
clean, grit free.
Place clams in shell
on the bottom of large steamer or canning pot. Pour in 2 cups
water.
Scrub,
but do not peel the Irish and sweet potatoes.
Put in pot over the clams.
Scrape carrot and place over
potatoes.
Place chicken, that has been salted and peppered, over
carrots.
Peel
onions;
place
in
pot
over chicken.
Put ears
of
corn,
shucked
and
silked
over the onions.
Cover pot.
Bring
to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat, but
maintain the boil.	The food steams and cooks in 1 hour.
If
sweet potato is tender, all is done.
Watch to see that the water does not cook out.

title: parmesan french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix seasoning, olive oil and Parmesan cheese in a large bowl.
Cut potatoes in strips; don't peel.
Toss with oil and Parmesan mixture.
Mixture will be dry.
Spread on nonstick or lightly greased baking pan in a single layer.
Bake at 475° for 30 minutes or until golden brown, tossing after 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs, mayonnaise, water and potato chips.
Mix water with mayonnaise and add to first mixture. Gently fold in eggs and top with potato chips.
Bake at 400° until bubbly, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix
first
ingredients and add 1/2 of stuffing mix. Pour in	casserole
dish,
9 x 13-inch.	Mix the other half of stuffing mix with melted margarine.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° or 400° until bubbly.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: crab dip
directions: Mix first six ingredients together gently until blended. Spread into 8 or 9-inch square glass pan.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Have plenty of crackers on hand for dipping.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in yolks and milk; blend well.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Reduce heat and stir occasionally for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla flavoring.
Layer wafers and bananas in bowl and pour custard over them.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread over top of pudding and bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until delicately brown. Serve warm or chilled.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions and bake in 8-inch layer pans (greased and floured).
When cake is cool, split layers in two.

title: caramel pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add gradually to sugar mixture.
Add milk and flavoring; beat well.
Pour into large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute oleo and onions, then add all other ingredients. Cook about 15 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: nut bread
directions: Bring 2 cups water to a boil.
Add the raisins and soda; cool 1/2 hour.
Beat the eggs with beater.
Add the sugar and beat together.
Sift the flour with 1 teaspoon salt.
Add the mixtures together; stir well.
Fold in the walnuts and add vanilla.
Have 4 pans well-greased and fill 3/4 full.
Bake a full hour at 350°.

title: pickled zucchini
directions: One day or up to 1 week ahead, cut zucchini into 1-inch chunks.
Thinly slice onion.
In a 2-quart saucepan over high heat, heat sugar, vinegar, pickling spice and bay leaves to boiling.
Add sliced onion; cook 1 minute.
Place zucchini in an 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Pour vinegar mixture over zucchini. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Stir occasionally. Drain before serving. Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with hot water.
Cool until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Let cool completely, then fold in package of whipped topping and oranges.
Chill until set.

title: beverly hills cheesecake
directions: Place oven rack in center of oven.
Heat to 350°.
Coat bottom and sides of nine-inch spring-form pan with cooking spray.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in lemon rind and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat at medium speed and add 1/2 cup sugar.
Very slowly beat until sugar is absorbed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Transfer pan to wire rack.
Do not turn off oven.
Mix sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Gently spread sour cream mixture over cake.
Return cake to oven.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Turn oven off.
Let cake stand in oven with door propped open for 30 minutes.
Cool cake completely.
Remove sides of pan.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Sift the dry ingredients.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla and work with spoon or hands until well blended.
Add 2 c. pecans.
Mix well.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Roll the balls in 1 c. pecans. Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until pale brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chiliques
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Last, layer with chips, meat mix, sour cream and cheese.
Heat thoroughly.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain the fruits 5 to 6 hours.
In a large bowl, mix fruit with remaining ingredients and put into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Put in 9 x 9-inch pan in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; cut into squares.

title: highland dinner
directions: Slice sausages 1/2-inch thick.
Brown slowly in large frypan. Remove with slotted spoon and set aside.
Shape ground meat into 1-inch balls, then roll in a mixture of flour, salt and pepper to coat well.
Brown in drippings of same frypan.
Remove and add to sausage.
Stir onion into pan and saute.
Stir in browned meat, bouillon cube, chili sauce, marjoram, rosemary and water, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling.

title: chicken salad balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Chill several hours. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: sawmill gravy
directions: Cook first four ingredients until brown.
Add milk and cook until thick.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Beat eggs and mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in buttered loaf pan.
Makes 2 loaves and can be cut in half.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse and drain shrimp well.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve with pretzels.

title: hearty potato sauerkraut soup
directions: In a 3 1/2 to 4-quart electric slow cooker, stir together all ingredients except bacon and eggs.
Cover and cook on low heat setting for 10 to 12 hours or until vegetables are tender.
If necessary, skim off fat before serving.
Sprinkle each serving with crisp bacon and chopped egg.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cucumber butter
directions: Place cucumber in blender; blend until smooth.
Whip margarine until light and fluffy in mixing bowl; gradually beat in cucumber. Blend in lemon juice, dill weed, onion, salt and Tabasco.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Great with fried yellow perch.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, mustard, celery seed, salt, pepper, onions and pickle.
Mix well.
Add potatoes and eggs; mix lightly. Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tang tea
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Brown chicken pieces in melted fat or butter.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Add seasonings.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add water or broth.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender. Place in a large covered casserole if your skillet is not ovenproof.
Blend flour and a little water; add sour cream and blend well.
Stir a little of the hot broth into sour cream, then return to skillet and blend.
Serve right away with dumplings.

title: pea salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-size pieces in a casserole dish. Separate onion rings and distribute evenly over lettuce.
Drain green peas; add to the lettuce and onion.
Spread mayonnaise over this; try to seal mixture evenly.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: pepper steak over rice
directions: Brown steak as per directions with diced onions and green peppers.
Cook tomatoes with a small amount of sugar.
Mix together and heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: mama's old-fashioned caramel pie
directions: Melt the 1 cup sugar in skillet.
Beat yolks and milk together.
Add liquid mixture to melted sugar and stir until all the sugar is dissolved.
(This will take several minutes.)
Mix the flour and sugar and add to the milk mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
You can use meringue or Cool Whip on top.

title: bull dog stew
directions: In a 10 to 16-quart pot, brown beef and onions together; pour off grease.
Chop chiles, peppers and jalapenos; mince garlic. Add all to pot with meat and onions.
Add half of chili powder, tomato paste and peeled tomatoes.
Chop tomatoes after putting in the pot.
Add 2 pints of water and 2 teaspoons salt.
Stir mixture in pot until thoroughly mixed.
Heat on medium-high, stirring often so as not to burn on bottom, until stew is bubbling.
Reduce heat to simmer; simmer for about 45 to 60 minutes, until chiles and peppers are very soft.
Add chili powder and salt to taste throughout process; cook water down to consistency desired.
If too spicy during taste checks throughout simmerimg time, add brown sugar to taste.
Serve hot; add cheese if desired to stew in bowls.
Enjoy!

title: flavored waters
directions: Fill blender container with water to within 1 1/2-inches of the top.
Add sugar, vanilla and strawberries.
Process until smoothly pureed.
Strain through sieve, discarding the fruit. Serve strained liquid over ice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: salmon stew
directions: Boil potatoes and chicken broth until tender. Add frozen vegetables (if used) ten all other ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Peel and boil the potatoes until almost done.
Slice the potatoes and layer with cheese, butter and jalapenos (should make 2 layers).
Add milk almost to the top of the pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: candied carrots
directions: Combine
butter,
sugar, carrots and water in saucepan. Cook over
low
heat
until carrots are tender.	Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Place allspice and cloves in a cheesecloth.
Mix all ingredients in large pan.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Dip out carefully.
Refrigerate leftovers and reheat.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and let stand 30 minutes. Cream the brown sugar, white sugar and oleo. Add the eggs and oatmeal mixture. Add the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Heat oven to 350°. Pour mixture into pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chilled marinated vegetable rice salad
directions: For Marinade:
Combine first five ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add vegetables to marinade and toss to cover.
Chill.
Add rice and toss lightly to combine.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into a ball, and cover with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: out of this world salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup liquid. Add Jell-O and boil 2 minutes.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and nuts, then whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries or nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix in order given, adding cheese last.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Stir and blend.
Add boiling water.
Add sugar and corn syrup.
Blend well.
Bring to a boil, not too hard, for 8 minutes.
Do not stir.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve hot.
Reheat over hot water.

title: diet soup(country:  u. s. a.)
directions: Cut up cabbage, onions and celery.
Add tomatoes, parsley and dill; boil 20 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add desired amount of cooked noodles and spaghetti sauce.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with desired toppings.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Saute onions
and mushrooms in margarine until tender.
Add garlic and parsley to soften.
Drain clams.
Add to mushrooms the liquid from 2 cans and retain liquid from third can.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: richard's wraps
directions: Soak cube steak in Dales overnight. Cut cube steak into small pieces (approximately the size of your thumb joint).
Cut bacon in half.
Cut cream cheese into small pieces (smaller than your thumbnail).
Pour peppers into bowl.
Take 1 piece of cube steak, 1 piece of cream cheese, 1 pepper and wrap together in bacon strip.
Place toothpick through wrap (to hold together as it cooks).
Repeat wraps until all ingredients are gone.
Continue to soak in Dales.
Place on hot grill for approximately 5 minutes, flip and repeat 5 minutes.
Eat & enjoy.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Beat eggs for 10 minutes.
Add vinegar, vanilla and sugar (beating after each addition).
Then add flour.
Pour in whipping cream, beating continuously.
Then add butter and nuts.
Mix well. Pour into shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or a little longer.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl, beat together, butter and cream cheese. Stir in corn, chilies, and onions; mixing well.
Pour into a greased 8x8-inch baking dish.

title: layered salad
directions: In an 8 x 13-inch Tupperware or airtight container, spread lettuce as bottom layer, then sprinkle onion, green pepper, celery and peas in turn.
Spread Miracle Whip over all as if it were frosting.
Sprinkle sugar over Miracle Whip, then sprinkle cheese and bacon bits.
Seal tightly.
Keep in refrigerator overnight. Best if served after 24 hours.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion in hot fat; add meat and seasonings.
Brown.
Add drained green beans and soup.
Pour into greased casserole.
Make instant mashed potatoes or real mashed potatoes and spoon into mounds over the meat.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add beans, tomato juice and chili powder.
Bring to boil for 1 to 2 minutes, then turn down to low heat.
Heat for 20 to 30 minutes and serve.

title: pineapple walnut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with icing while still warm.

title: turkey picatta
directions: Drizzle 1 tablespoon lemon juice over cutlets; set aside. Combine flour, paprika and pepper; dredge cutlets in flour mixture.
Heat oil in a large, nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add turkey and cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until browned.
Transfer to a serving platter; keep warm.

title: holiday cranberry punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Combine in punch bowl.
Float holly wreath ring on top, if desired.
Yields 50 servings.

title: low-fat milk shake
directions: Put 1 cup milk and 1/4 teaspoon sugar into blender on lowest setting.
Blend for 1 minute.
Add banana and blend for 2 more minutes.

title: pineapple appetizer
directions: Soak pineapple chunks in creme de menthe for about an hour before dinner and chill in refrigerator.
Serve before dinner with toothpicks.

title: microwave cake recipes
directions: Hand mix all ingredients until moist.
Do not use mixer or beat by hand.
Spoon mixture evenly in a 3-quart microwave casserole dish with cone insert.
Microwave on High for 12 to 14 minutes on rotating carousel.

title: cornmeal rolls(4 dozen)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, cornmeal, the sugar, 1/2 cup butter, eggs, salt and 2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make dough easy to handle. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken; debone.
Cook noodles.
Saute Ro-Tel and mushrooms in stick of margarine.
Grate cheese.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° until bubbly, about 25 minutes.

title: cherry dream cream
directions: Drain both cans of pineapple and put in bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients with pineapple.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate chip cookies("healthy cuisine for kids")
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 2 baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium sized bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Melt butter in a small saucepan over low heat.
Cook, swirling the butter in the pan, until butter turns nutty brown, 30 to 60 seconds.
Pour into large mixing bowl. Add cream cheese, brown sugar and white sugar.
Beat with electric mixer on low until smooth.
Add egg, egg white and vanilla.
Beat until well incorporated.
Add the reserved flour mixture and chocolate chips.
Stir with wooden spoon just until combined.
(The batter will be runny.)

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add seasoning mix, water and tomato paste according to directions on seasoning mix.
In a separate pot, heat (do not boil) sour cream, soup and diced chilies.

title: 'unfried' southern fried chicken
directions: In a large bowl, cover chicken with buttermilk and salt. Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.
Drain.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Cut asparagus in about 1/2-inch pieces.
Slice scallions thin and chop the tops.
Add all ingredients except flour and milk to chicken stock.
Simmer until tender.
Mix flour in a little bit of the milk to make a smooth mix.
When asparagus is tender, add milk and flour mix.
Stir until soup comes to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer a few minutes.

title: ham and spinach rolls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add stuffing and sour cream.
Spread on ham slices; roll up and place seam side down in shallow baking dish.
Melt butter; stir in flour and add milk.
Cook and stir slowly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add Cheddar.
Remove from heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over ham. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes. May be made ahead and frozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients. Combine with zucchini mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Makes 2 loaves and 4 small ones. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Grease and flour pans.

title: peanut butter ice cream topping
directions: Mix all together.
Serve over ice cream.

title: hot corn
directions: Slice peppers.
Mix peppers with corn.
Dump cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: scotch a roos
directions: Melt first three ingredients together.
Cook slowly until dissolved, not grainy.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in double boiler.
Pour on top of above mix.
Let sit until cool.
It's yummy!

title: people chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips together in microwave or on stove.
Stir into cereal; pour powdered sugar on mixture.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Grease a large bread pan (one with a rim). Line pan with wax paper or foil. Grease paper or spray with Pam. Pour batter into pan. (Should be very thin.) Cook 12 to 15 minutes at 375°. DO NOT OVERCOOK. Cool about 5 minutes. Turn cake out onto a clean thin towel and remove foil. Roll cake up in the towel (like a jellyroll). Mix cream cheese, margarine, vanilla and confectioners sugar. Unroll cake and spread with filling, keeping thin near the edges so it doesn't squish out. Re-roll and refrigerate.

title: salad or dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Makes 3 (1 pound) bowls.
Can be frozen.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes with 3 1/2 cups of 10x sugar reserving the last 1/4 cup for rolling out dough mixture.
Sprinkle the 1/4 cup sugar on a flat surface and roll mixture into a rectangular shape approximately 1/8 inch thick.
Spread with peanut butter and roll width-wise to form a long snake.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate. Slice into pinwheel shape.

title: 3 layer pudding cake
directions: Pat in an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mock apple pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine all except crackers.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add crackers to mixture and boil for 2 minutes.
Do not stir.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell; top with dabs of butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Top with lattice-top crust and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Tastes just like apple pie!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar and syrup in saucepan over low heat.
Add peanuts and increase heat a little.
Cook until peanuts are done, stirring frequently.
The nuts will begin to pop when getting done.
Do not overcook as candy will continue to cook.
Add soda and stir thoroughly.
Pour on large buttered cookie sheet or 2 smaller ones.
Stretch thin.
Be sure to use flexable as the candy will come out easier.
Let cool completely before trying to get it out and break it up.

title: pound cake
directions: In large bowl, using mixer at medium speed, beat first four ingredients until light (2 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition (total beating time: 10 minutes). Add flour; blend well.

title: heart and healthy stir-fry(serve over hot cooked rice.)
directions: Combine water, soy sauce, cornstarch and sugar.
Heat 1/2 of oil in skillet; add vegetables and stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or a little longer.
Remove vegetables to another bowl.
Add rest of oil and meat, not more than 1/3 at a time.
Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until meat is done.
Add soy mixture and cook until thick and clear.
Add vegetables and garlic powder until heated. Serve over cooked rice.

title: soft cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs; combine with first mixture.
Add in dry ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Put a heaping teaspoon of dough on a greased baking sheet.
Then press down with a glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until browned.
This recipe is easily halved.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls on a cookie sheet.
Press edges together.
Bake according to the directions on package.
Cool.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Blend in flour and nutmeg.
Slowly stir in chicken broth and water.
Then bring to a boil, while stirring.
Now add cauliflowerets, then simmer soup, covered, about 25 minutes or until cauliflowerets are tender.

title: chicken caribbean
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
In 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken until browned on all sides.
In cup, combine remaining ingredients; pour mixture over chicken and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover skillet and simmer 35 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, basting frequently with liquid in skillet.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving pieces and brown in a pan over surface heat. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours. Spoon the sauce over the ribs 2 or 3 times during baking. Bake uncovered 15 minutes more.

title: black-eyed pea, sausage and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, sausage and peppers until sausage is browned; drain off grease.
In a large oblong dish, mix rice, soup mix and water.
Add meat mixture and peas.
Mix well.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and fruit cocktail and let set a while in the refrigerator.
When beginning to get thick, pour over cake in a container with a lid.
Then shake back and forth to cover cake all over.
Then turn cake upside down.
Leave in refrigerator until sets.
Turn out on a cake plate.
Slice and serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour, alternating with milk a little at a time.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350°.
After cake starts to brown, lower temperature to 325° until cake is done.
Use tube pan.
Be sure to grease.

title: sunday rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let sit 5 minutes, until bubbly.
Mix hot water, honey, oil and salt until honey completely dissolves.
Add eggs and stir well.
Add yeast and flour.
Mix well.
(Add more flour if it sticks to fingers.)
Shape dough into any type rolls and allow to rise.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 425°.

title: beef burgers provencale
directions: Combine ground beef, 1/4 cup zucchini and bread crumbs; form into patties.
Brown for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in remaining zucchini and pizza sauce.
Bring to boil, reduce heat; cover and simmer 7 to 9 minutes, until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Add can of potatoes and simmer for 3 minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: vermont maple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Measure flour.
Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Blend in.
Mix in nuts.
Chill dough if soft.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake about 10 minutes or until almost no imprint remains when touched lightly.
Spread with Maple Butter Glaze.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt cheese in mushroom soup.
Pour over thawed potatoes in dish.
Cook in 350° oven until brown.

title: ina's wacky, wild cubes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Freeze in ice cube trays.
Add cubes as desired to tea.
(Nice in herbal iced teas, especially mango.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix the soup, pepper and salt (to taste), milk and water.
In casserole dish, spread 1 layer of potatoes.
Put 1/2 of the soup mixture on top.
Cut up 1/2 small onion over it.
Repeat another layer. Cook in a 350° oven until golden brown or until the potatoes are tender, approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix ingredient together and pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: texas bars
directions: Mix caramels and 1/3 cup milk in heavy saucepan and set aside. Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup milk, melted butter and nuts.
Press 3/4 of this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture on, then crumble remaining cake mix over this. Return to oven for 15 minutes longer.
Cook, then cut into squares.

title: pickled beets and eggs
directions: Drain juice from beets and add water, sugar, vinegar and spices.
Boil 5 minutes and remove from heat and add beets. Peeled eggs may be added now or later.
Allow to stand at least overnight, refrigerated.
The longer the eggs remain in the beet juice the deeper the red color penetrates into the egg.
More hard-cooked eggs may be added, if desired.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, milk, eggs, soda, salt and corn together.
Brown meat and drain.
Pour layer of cornbread mixture in a greased floured skillet.
Put on meat, cheese, onions and pepper.
Pour on rest of cornbread mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brother george
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
In frypan, brown meat and onion; drain grease.
Add soups and sauce and heat through. Mix in drained noodles and coat.
Turn half the mixture into 2-quart baking dish.
Layer with slices of Velveeta cheese, then top with rest of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beets and pineapple
directions: Put beets in saucepan with drained pineapple and brown sugar.

title: lime velvet salad
directions: Dissolve jello, 1 1/2 cups hot water, 1 cup cold water and 1 cup fruit juice.
Cool and add drained pineapple and pears.
Then fold in sour cream.
Makes 12 to 14 good sized molds.

title: icebox bread and butter pickles
directions: You will also need 1 large pickle jar (glass).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Drain shrimp and soak in ice water for at least 20 minutes.
(This is very important.) Then add shrimp to the other mixture.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine spices, sugar and salt.
Combine with cider and lemon; simmer 12 minutes.
Strain and reheat.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: super-duper fruit salad
directions: Combine frozen strawberries and vanilla pudding.
Drain oranges, pineapple chunks, sliced peaches, sliced pears and fruit cocktail.
Add fruit to strawberries and pudding mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Mix baking powder and cracker crumbs.
Add to mixture, alternating with milk, beating well.
After each addition, beat 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in greased and floured cake pans.
Makes 3 layers.

title: cherry creams
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy, 2-quart saucepan.
In pan, combine sugar, water, cream and corn syrup.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon to dissolve sugar.
This should take 5 to 6 minutes.
Avoid splashing mixture on sides of pan.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Combine all of the first 3 ingredients except 2/3 cup cake mix. Mix until crumbly and press into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until golden.

title: fudgy brownie cutouts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line an 8-inch square baking pan with foil; spray foil with vegetable cooking spray.
In small mixer bowl, stir together granulated sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add applesauce, egg whites and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter into prepared pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are firm.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Place in freezer about 15 minutes for easier cutting.
Lift brownies from pan using sides of foil; carefully peel off foil.
With small cookie cutters, cut brownies into desired shapes or cut into squares.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Mix butter, dates, sugar and eggs.
Put in frying pan and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Put Rice Krispies and walnuts in bowl.
Pour mixture over and stir.
When cool, shape into walnut size balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: crock-pot applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well. Beat in applesauce.
Combine flour, soda and spices and stir into creamed mixture.
Blend in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured bread and cake pan and cover.
Place in crock-pot; cover and bake on high setting for 2 1/2 t 4 hours.
Makes 24 servings. Recipe for 5-quart crock-pot.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut pork and chicken into strips and slice mushrooms lengthwise and saute one after the other in hot oil in a heavy skillet.
Turn frequently.
Return pork, bamboo shoots, celery and onion to skillet.
Set aside mushrooms and chicken.
Add broth and garlic. Season with salt, pepper and sugar.
Cover and bring to a boil. Combine soy sauce, ginger and sherry.
Add cornstarch mixed with water.
Stir into hot mixture and cook until thickened.
Add chicken and mushrooms.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve with rice.

title: polvorones de carnela
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.

Add flour, 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon, salt and vanilla, making a moderately stiff dough; chill few hours, then roll into small balls, about 1-inch. Bake on buttered cookie sheet at 400° for 14 to 17 minutes.
Roll in 2 cups confectioners sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon mixture while hot; cool and roll in mixture again.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion; saute.
Stir in flour, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Add broth.
Stir to mix well.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in chicken and vegetables. Heat until bubbly.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake until brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients using enough milk to make mixture smooth. Drop mixture by spoonfuls into deep fat (380°) or oil. Cook until golden brown. Drain and serve.

title: squash au gratin
directions: Boil tender squash with a little onion.
Cream well while warm.
Add butter, cheese, eggs (beaten lightly) and 1 tablespoon bread crumbs to make light batter.
Reserve a little of the bread crumbs and cheese.
Put in casserole; cover with bread crumbs and the cheese.
Bake.

title: angel food cake
directions: Measure and sift together first 2 ingredients three times. Measure the rest of the ingredients, except sugar, in a large bowl.
Beat until foamy.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, a little at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Bake at 375° on bottom rack of oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jam muffins
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, egg and milk to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly with a fork until the dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter should be lumpy.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups until they are half full.
Add 1 teaspoon of jam.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: tasty pot roast
directions: Rub salt into roast. Place in a large pan. Add dry mustard, cinnamon, nutmeg, onions, garlic, bay leaves and oil. Cover and cook slowly for 2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and put in bottom of dish.
Drain green beans and pour them over beef.
Sprinkle with garlic salt. Pour tomato soup over green beans.
Drop spoonfuls of potatoes on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until soup is bubbling.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Mix with celery, onion, cheese and mayonnaise.
Put into casserole dish and crumble Ritz crackers over evenly.
Pour margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: chipped ham sauce
directions: Brown the butter, celery and onion until tender.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir, simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 pounds Polish ham, sliced thin.

title: orange salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in jello and hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add orange sherbet, Cool Whip and mandarin oranges. Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef sirloin in 1/4-inch strips.
Coat meat with mixture of 1 tablespoon flour and salt.
Heat cooking utensil over direct heat.
Then add 2 tablespoons butter.
When melted, cook sirloin strips quickly until brown on all sides.
Add sliced mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes until onion is crisp-tender.
Remove from pan.

title: elsie's cream cheese cherry pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Pour mixture into crust.
Chill until set, (2 or 3 hours).
Top with pie filling.
Dig in! Love Mom.

title: gooey butter cream cheese cake
directions: Mix all together and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: squirrel mulligan
directions: Stew squirrels and reserve broth.
Remove meat from bones and put back in broth.
Bring to a boil and add all ingredients, except rice.
Cook about 45 minutes or until all vegetables are tender.
Add cooked rice and serve hot.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and cheese.
Add sugar and cream well. Add vanilla.
Slowly add the flour; mix well.
Put through a cookie press.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Watch, they burn very fast.

title: artichoke dip
directions: In an ovenproof bowl, combine the mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Drain and chop the artichoke hearts and add to the mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve immediately with assorted crackers.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes. Makes 2 quarts.
Spray bowl with Pam.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of the milk and the vanilla as directed on the package, using large mixing bowl.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and the pudding mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir in coconut. Spoon into pie shell. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Saute onion in small amount of butter.
Pour all ingredients into crock-pot and heat on high 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Melt butter
and chocolate in a heavy saucepan over low heat. Pour into a medium-size bowl; cool slightly.
Add eggs, sugar and corn
syrup.
Beat	with
rotary beater until well-blended.
Stir in	vanilla
and
pecans.
Pour
mixture
into unbaked shell. Bake on lower shelf of a moderate oven at 375° for 40
minutes. Cool thoroughly.
Top with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream, if you wish.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugars until fluffy. Stir in molasses, beaten egg yolks and egg whites until foamy. Blend 1 3/4 cups flour into mixture and baking powder; dissolve brandy, sherry and spices, stirring well.
Dredge fruits and nuts in a bowl with the 1/2 cup flour.
Fold cake mixture in with fruits; pack into a well greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in slow oven, cool and wrap in foil.
Store in airtight container.
Set oven temperature at 350°; bake time is 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter baking sheets.
Combine flour, cornstarch, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat the 1/4 pound butter with peanut butter.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Press a chocolate kiss, flat side down, into each ball and then press dough up sides of kiss until only point is visible.
Put cookies on baking sheets, spacing about 2-inches apart.
Bake until lightly browned at edges and beginning to brown on top, about 10 minutes.
Total Time:
1 hour.
Makes 35. Calories:

title: skillet macaroni cheese
directions: Melt butter in a large, covered skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until tender, but do not brown.
Stir while cooking.
Add flour and salt, stirring to make a fine paste.
Add milk, stirring as you add, making a smooth mix.
Add macaroni. Cover skillet and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Do not allow mixture to boil.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook sugar and buttermilk in iron skillet.
Stir often.
Cook to soft ball candy stage.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir; add pecans.
Set off heat; stir until sugary.
Pour into greased platter and cut.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: At 425°, heat a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients except drippings.
Pour drippings in the bottom of pan.
Pour batter over drippings and bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with beef.

title: french dressing
directions: Put ingredients in a quart jar and shake well each time you use. Refrigerate.

title: five hour stew
directions: Stir all together to distribute tapioca. Cover and cook in 250° oven at least 5 hours. May be cooked at 300° for 4 hours. Do not peek!

title: portuguese homemade flan pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, 8 tablespoons sugar and 1 cup of milk.
Beat at high speed until mixed well.
Then gradually add in the remaining 3 cups of milk and continue beating it at high speed until mix runs clear.
Add the extract and beat again for 1 minute.

title: noodle hamburger casserole
directions: Add 1 can milk to each can of soup.
Cook noodles; drain.
Fry hamburg and onion, celery and pepper, browning slightly.
Mix hamburg with soups and alternate with noodles in baking dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Remove 1/2 cup of cookie dough and reserve for another use. Add flour to remaining dough; knead with hands to combine.
Press in a 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cookie is lightly browned.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Loosen cookie from pizza pan.
Cut into squares now.
Cool completely.

title: sandy's snapper scandinavian(i had it in denmark - delicious!!!)
directions: Arrange fish in a single layer in a buttered shallow baking pan.
Season with next 5 ingredients.
Pour tomatoes over fish. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pockets
directions: Pick chicken off bone; lay aside.
Melt butter in large saucepan; add Mozzarella, 1/2 Cheddar and sour cream.
Stir over low heat until melted.
Add soups.
Add dash of salt and pinch of garlic; simmer.
Butter baking pan.
Roll out biscuits or croissants.
In middle, place bits of chicken.
Spoon sauce; close pocket and seal edges.
Continue to fill pan with pockets.
Bake in a 350° oven.
When bread rises (about 10 minutes), spoon a little sauce over top of pockets, then sprinkle with remaining Cheddar. Bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: souper chicken
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of baking dish.
Layer dried beef and chicken breast in dish.
Combine soup and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Pour Kool-Aid and sugar into boiling water. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add other ingredients and freeze until slushy. Makes 3 gallons.

title: shower punch
directions: Heat sugar and 1/2 gallon of water in a large saucepan until sugar melts.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Freeze the day before.
Remove from freezer; thaw slightly.
Add 2 large bottles of ginger ale.

title: quickie strawberry pie
directions: Clean and wash berries.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together and add
to
the
berries.
Cover
one 9-inch pie pan with bottom crust
and
pour
in
the
berry mixture.
Dot the berries with butter and
cover
with the top crust.
Bake in a very hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate oven at 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add alternately with the sour cream, blending well.
Add vanilla.
Mix the nuts, flour, cinnamon and brown sugar.
In a greased and lightly floured Bundt pan, spread 3 alternate layers of batter and filling, beginning with the batter and ending with the filling.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: buttermilk brownie cake
directions: Combine butter, water and cocoa in heavy saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Stir hot cocoa mixture into batter.
Beat by hand until well mixed.
Pour into a jelly roll pan which has been greased and floured on bottom only.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
While cake is warm, pour Chocolate Buttermilk Frosting on top and spread evenly.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add chicken broth and milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce is thick and bubbly. Add chicken and mushrooms.
Serve over rice, toast, or biscuits.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon soy sauce and cayenne pepper.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Stir-fry cucumber, celery and pepper in 1 tablespoon hot oil in skillet.
Add cooked chicken to vegetables and heat through.
Remove chicken and vegetables and reserve.

title: snow peas with almonds
directions: Combine water, soy sauce, cornstarch and bouillon; set aside. Melt butter in 10-inch skillet; add almonds.
Stir-fry 2 minutes. Add mushrooms, drained.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 or 2 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: egg salad sandwich
directions: Peel eggs, and mash with fork.
Add mayonnaise, salt, pepper, and celery; mix well.
Spread evenly on bread.
Serve.

title: connie's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, boil and cool.
Take meat off bone.
Combine soups and sour cream.
Put chicken into prepared 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Top with cracker and poppy seed mixture.
Pour melted butter over the topping.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil
chicken until tender.
Use broth to cook spaghetti. Drain
(not dry).
Add chopped chicken and soup.
Stir in small can
pimento
(chopped)
and
parsley
flakes, salt and pepper. Put
in
baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 300°. May sprinkle
grated
cheese,
if desired, just before taking from oven.
This freezes well.

title: escarole soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts in 6-quarts of water.
Simmer several hours until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken parts to cool on plate.
Shred white meat with fingers to check that all small bones are removed.
Return white meat to soup, reduced to about 4 quarts (add water, if needed).
Wash and drain escarole leaves and cut into long, narrow crosscut parts.
Add to soup 1/2 hour before servings.
Whip egg and drizzle into broth.
Add 2 tablespoons of Locatelli cheese.
Season to taste.
Serve piping hot with cheese on side.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.
Add water to maintain volume over simmering time.
Serves about 8 with seconds.

title: pecan pie
directions: With a pastry brush, brush inside of pie shell with egg white. Let dry at room temperature at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: crab toast
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl, except English muffins. Scoop mixture onto quartered English muffins and place in freezer on a paper plate until almost frozen and hard. Once hard, place in a large Ziploc freezer bag until needed.

title: easy pastry
directions: Melt oleo or butter in pie pan.
Add flour, sugar and baking powder.
Press out in pan.
Pour filling in and bake.
Very good.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel sweet potatoes or yams and cut into small chunks so they will be tender.
Cook until done, rinse, drain and then mash.
Add margarine and sugar and mix well.
Add milk, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon and mix well.
Pour into uncooked pie shells.
Cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until firm in center.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix Velveeta cheese, cream cheese, lemon juice, garlic powder and red pepper.
Roll into ball.
Roll in chili powder and paprika.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Cook blueberries and thicken with cornstarch as you would for a pie.
Mix jello with 2 cups hot water.
Add nuts and pineapple. Let set overnight, then spread sour cream over top.

title: mama's biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Stir in buttermilk. Turn out dough onto floured board. Sprinkle with more flour.
Pat or roll out dough to about 3/4-inch thickness. Cut out biscuits.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, vegetables and salt.
Mix well.
Combine cream cheese and remaining ingredients, mixing well until blended. Add to macaroni mixture; mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice and seafood salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Season to taste. Chill.
Serve on salad greens.
Garnish with tomato wedges. Great summertime dish.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Add enough water to reserved mandarin orange juice to equal 1 cup.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and juice/water mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oranges and peel.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into cooked pie shell.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: In bowl mix mustard, mayonnaise, sugar, garlic salt, black pepper and dry Italian seasoning.
Add onion, dill pickles and pimento.
Mix and add can of peas.
Mix all together and let set for a few hours in refrigerator.
Can also add chopped ham.

title: tuna and shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions and drain well. Cool.
Combine cooked shells with remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Chill.
Garnish with parsley and paprika before serving.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Close and shake until potatoes are evenly coated. Empty potatoes in shallow baking dish.
Stir occasionally.
Bake 40 minutes or until tender.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: baked chicken -n- rice
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix soup and rice in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes or until done.

title: pantry-shelf clam sauce
directions: This is great when you want something in no time.
Serves 2.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown 1 1/2 pounds ground beef and chopped onion in pan. Shred 1/2 medium cabbage.
In casserole dish, layer shredded cabbage in bottom of dish.
Then put alternate layers of meat and cabbage in dish.
Pour and spread tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cabbage is done.

title: maine crab cakes, chesapeake style
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together until well blended.
Saute the pepper and onion in a little butter until soft.
Add to mayonnaise mixture.
Gently fold in crabmeat.
Shape into 2-inch patties. Saute in butter over medium-high heat until brown on both sides.
Makes 6 to 8 (2-inch) cakes.

title: irish scoon recipe
directions: Mix sifted baking powder, salt, flour and sugar together. Meanwhile, soak raisins in boiling water.
Drain them and mix in flour.
Beat egg and add milk.
Mix (don't beat) well; add to flour.
Bake in 9-inch square or round pans in a preheated 375° oven for 3/4 hour.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and peanut butter. Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour, soda and salt. add to sugar mixture.
Form dough into balls and flatten with a fork. Bake at 325° for 8 minutes. Let cookies cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: shrimp croquettes
directions: Heat butter in a skillet.
Fry shrimp until pink in color. Add garlic and onion.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add mixture of flour and milk.
Cook until smooth and thick, stirring frequently.
Remove and cool.
Divide into 12 equal portions.
Shape each portion into an oval shaped ball.
Dip in egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry in oil until browned.

title: special egg breakfast
directions: Mix eggs, garlic powder, milk, salt and sour cream in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top this mixture with diced ham or crumbled cooked sausage, Cheddar cheese and onion.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Excellent with hash browns and sweet rolls.

title: becky's poor man's lobster
directions: Marinate chicken in mixture of all other ingredients for 3 hours.
Broil for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once.

title: real italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, celery, garlic and onion.
Put all ingredients in a large pot and simmer.
We usually simmer this all day and plan to have spaghetti the next day.

title: touchdown chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts. Cool 10 to 12 minutes.
On aluminum foil-lined baking sheet, shape into a smooth ball, then into a football shape.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Place on serving plate.
Garnish as desired.
Store, covered, at room temperature.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar once when warm and again when cool.

title: egg salad sandwich
directions: Have an adult boil or cook the egg for you.
After it is cool, have someone help chop the egg into small pieces.
In a bowl, mix the egg, mayonnaise or salad dressing and relish. Carefully add seasonings to your taste. Arrange extras on your bread, such as lettuce, tomatoes, bacon.
Spread the egg mixture on the other slice of bread.
Makes filling for 1 sandwich.

title: appetizer hot sugared sausages
directions: Wrap each sausage or cut portion with 1/3 slice of bacon and fasten with toothpick.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Cover with brown sugar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until bacon is browned.
Serve hot and keep hot to serve.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir mixture together and drain well.
Put in pan with 1 quart vinegar (add more if needed), sugar and pickling spice (tied in a rag); cook for 35 to 45 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Add all ingredients except pecans to sour cream.
Mix with hands well until blended.
Form into ball.
Roll in pecans, if desired.
Serve with crackers.
Suggest serving with Wheat Thins or Sociables.

title: chef gail's chicken pate
directions: Saute garlic and shallots in olive oil until translucent. Drain livers. Add to saute pan and cook about 3 minutes until browned. Pour in Madeira and deglaze pan. Cook until Madeira is almost gone. Remove from heat and cool for 5 minutes. Place mixture in a food processor and mix until smooth, using quick on and off turns. With motor running, add the butter a little at a time and process until the butter is well mixed and the mixture is very smooth. Taste and adjust with salt and pepper. Scrape mixture into a ball bowl or terrene; cover with plastic wrap and chill at least 3 hours. Serve with crackers or toasted bread rounds.

title: easy chicken and "whop" dumplins
directions: Boil chicken about 30 minutes.
Open canned biscuits and "Whop" on cabinet or stove.
Carefully pinch or cut biscuits and add to boiling water.
After all the biscuits are in and the water has returned to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste, and simmer another 20 - 30 minutes.
Umm Ummm good!

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs lightly.
Stir milk, oil and brown sugar into eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix quickly by stirring.
Add nuts, if desired.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake at 375°
for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 very large muffins.

title: jiffy onion bread
directions: Saute the onion in the oil.
Combine milk and beaten egg in small bowl.
Blend Bisquick into milk and egg mixture.
Add onion and Cheddar cheese.
Spread with other cheese and seed.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven.
Serve warm; cut into wedges.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight container (I use Tupperware).
Put 3 to 4 teaspoons per cup of boiling water (or amount to suit your taste).

title: easy peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together margarine, peanut butter and sugar.
Pat mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 15 to 30 minutes.
Melt milk chocolate in microwave on Low or melt in double boiler.
When chocolate is creamy, spread over peanut butter mixture. Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
This is sweeter than Reese's.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix bread crumbs with margarine.
Place bread cubes in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add sausage, mushrooms and cheese.
Mix eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard.
Pour over ingredients in casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, bring to room temperature. Mix soup with 1/2 can milk.
Pour over casserole.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 75 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Bake a 9-inch deep dish pastry at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove and prick; bake 5 more minutes.
Cool.
Mix the first 4 ingredients well, then add the next 3.
Pour into precooked pastry and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until set.

title: lime strawberry surprise holiday delight
directions: Prepare lime gelatin and add drained crushed pineapple.
Chill until slightly thick.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: white mountain cream frosting
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, water and corn syrup.
When it strings a thread 6 to 8 inches, beat over the beaten egg whites and add vanilla.

title: overnight apple french toast
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and corn syrup until thick.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13 inch pan, arrange apples on top of syrup.
In a bowl, beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Dip bread in egg mixture and arrange over top of apples.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking and uncover.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes or until top is browned.

title: raisin spice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Store in refrigerator or freeze.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Boil cabbage leaves that have been separated for about 3 or 4 minutes. Place meat, rice, salt, pepper and cinnamon in bowl and mix well. If leaves are large, cut in halves. Stuff and roll with meat mixture into small firm rolls. Arrange the rolls in a cooking pot in layers and place 2 cloves of garlic between each layer. Cover with a dish in the pot and add water, tomatoes, tomato paste and salt. Cover and cook for 1/2 hour.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Cook, skin, bone and cut the chicken into bite size pieces. Place chicken, pimento, seasonings and vegetables in a large casserole dish. Mix and spread the next 4 ingredients evenly before topping with the bread crumbs. Serve over a bed of rice.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Fold all together and pour into two graham cracker pie shells. Refrigerate until firm.

title: butter roll
directions: Stir milk into the 2 cups flour, mixing well.
Add melted shortening.
Knead in enough flour to make a soft biscuit dough. Roll out biscuit dough to 1/2-inch or less thickness.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour, sugar, butter and vanilla together and spread on biscuit dough.
Roll up jelly roll style and place in a cake pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cover with hot water.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashion raisin pie
directions: Combine raisins and water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Blend sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Add to raisins and cook, stirring until clear.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and margarine.
Cool slightly.
Put into pastry lined pie pan.
Cover with top pastry or lattice strips.
Bake at 425° about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: orange bowl coffee cake
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine in bowl 1/4 cup sugar, the butter, salt and milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in eggs, orange juice and yeast.
Gradually add flour to form a stiff dough; knead on floured surface until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease all sides.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients.
Spread on muffin halves; cut into 8 wedges (or smaller).
Freeze on cookie sheet; store them when frozen in plastic bag in freezer.
To serve, take out and broil for a few minutes.
Makes approximately 96 appetizers.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to boiling point.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Place each slice of bread in a 1 1/2-quart dish face in the bowl.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt gradually.
Stir in scalded milk.
Pour over bread.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Sprinkle nutmeg.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° until is solid, 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, baking powder, soda and salt.
Heat applesauce, sugars, egg substitute and vanilla; add to dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets and bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Melt the chocolate bits, Eagle Brand milk and salt over low heat.
Add the nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in covered container.
Use about 1/3 cup of mixture in a cup and fill with boiling water.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Pour into cooled baked pie shell.
Spread meringue atop pie and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening;
gradually
add
sugar, beating well. Add eggs; mix
well.
Stir
in
pumpkin
and
water.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to creamed mixutre.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° in 2 well greased
and floured loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Boil roast until very tender (approximately 3 to 4 hours). Add water to cover roast as it boils down.
When roast is tender, let water boil almost out.
Cool roast, tear it off the bone and remove fatty parts.

title: sausage-rice pilaf
directions: Fry sausage slices until lightly browned; drain and set aside. Brown rice in melted oleo over medium heat.
Add onions and celery; saute.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add sausage and cover.
Cook over low heat for 25 to 30 minutes, or until rice is cooked.

title: chicken oriental noodle dish
directions: Melt margarine in
pan.
Add
vegetables and cook until they are heated through (or to desired doneness).
Prepare the noodles as stated on the package, but do not put the seasoning in yet. Drain the noodles and add them to the vegetables.
Add the chopped chicken and the seasoning package.	Mix lightly.

title: corn chowder
directions: Remove corn from cobs.
Place cobs in large soup pot.
Cover with 1/2 gallon of milk.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Remove cobs from milk.
Cool enough to handle.
With back of spoon, scrape corn cobs.
Discard cobs.
Pour scrapings along with fresh corn, potatoes and onion in milk.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: teriyaki meatballs
directions: Combine ground meat with rest of ingredients.
Form in tiny balls, 1-inch across.
Place in large roasting pan and bake, uncovered, at 275° for one hour.
Makes about 100 meatballs.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Mix flour, pecans and margarine. Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Mix cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar. Spread over first mixture. Mix pudding mixes and 3 cups milk. Pour over second mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over third mixture and chill.
Top with chopped pecans and grated Hershey bar.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in baking dish.
Mix together bread cubes, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper, melted butter and 1/4 cup water.
Press bread mixture on top of chops.
Mix together mushroom soup and 1/3 cup water; heat.
Pour soup over bread mixture; cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cranberry whipped cream salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Add boiling water to make 1 cup. Dissolve jello in hot liquid.
Stir in cranberry sauce and orange peel. Chill until partially set.
Fold in orange slices and pineapple. Whip the cream and fold into fruit mixture.
Pour into mold. Chill until set.
Unmold. Garnish with grapes and cranberries dipped in egg white and rolled in lime or raspberry gelatin.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: On medium-high boil chicken along with onion, salt and pepper, garlic powder and chicken bouillon cubes about 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from pot and cut into small pieces.
Combine chicken, 2 cups of egg noodles and corn and cook on medium heat for approximately 15 minutes.
Cut hard-boiled eggs into small pieces and add to pot.
Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.

title: hot and spicy pepper and apricot chutney
directions: Combine sweet red peppers, apricots, raisins, onion, garlic, ginger root, salt and red pepper flakes, cumin seed, mustard seed and sugar into large saucepan.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, over medium heat until sugar dissolves, about 5 minutes.
Add vinegar. Cook, stirring often, until mixture is shiny and thick, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate. Good served with cream cheese and crackers.

title: shrimp in beer batter
directions: Peel and devein the shrimp.
Put flour in mixing bowl.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg and coriander.
Gradually add the beer, stirring with a wire whisk until smooth.
Brush the top of the batter with 1 teaspoon oil.
This prevents gas from escaping. Cover with plastic wrap and let stand in warm place for 30 minutes.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix and form 1/2 teaspoon into ball.
Shape as strawberry. Roll in red sugar.
Green icing.
Wear rubber gloves to make.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into
a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.

title: fresh cucumber relish
directions: Slice cucumbers in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds and discard.
With food chopper, using coarse blade, grind cucumbers and onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: smoked rice
directions: Saute celery and onion until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer lettuce, peas, peppers, onions and celery.
Top with Miracle Whip.
Smooth and seal over all. Sprinkle with sugar, cheese and bacon.
Chill overnight, covered.

title: sopaipilla(mexican bread)
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut Crisco in flour with pastry blender.
Add egg.
Add water.
Roll out and cut in triangles and deep fry.
Serve with beans or honey.

title: homemade cream cheese ice cream
directions: Warm milk, sugar and vanilla in large pan.
Let cool slightly. Add a small portion of milk mixture to softened cream cheese and mix until smooth.
Add cream cheese into milk mixture, then add half and half.
Beat with mixer to blend cream cheese in well. Pour into ice cream maker and crank until done.

title: low-fat layered mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order on serving dish.

title: cream of cucumber soup
directions: Peel, seed and chop coarsely the cucumbers.
Set aside.
In medium size saucepan, saute the onion in butter until tender.
Add the cucumber.
Cover with stock and simmer for 30 minutes.
Puree in a blender until smooth.
Correct seasoning; add the sour cream and blend again.
Refrigerate until ready to serve, topped with chives.

title: beef  and noodle casserole
directions: Saute the meat, onion and pepper. Add other ingredients.
Add to cooked noodles. Top with cheese and heat in a 350° oven.

title: hungarian stuffed peppers
directions: Combine the first six ingredients and stuff peppers.
Cook in tomato sauce 1 hour.

title: caramel icing
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil on low heat for 12 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until ready to spread cake.

title: yummy vegetable pizza
directions: Separate crescent roll dough into rectangles.
Arrange in nonstick baking pan, pressing edges and perforations to seal. Bake at 375° using package directions.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion salt, garlic powder and dill weed in bowl; mix well.
Spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with peas, celery, tomatoes, broccoli and carrots.
Cut into small wedges.

title: spanish waxed beans
directions: Cut bacon into small 1-inch pieces; cook in heavy pan until crisp.
Add chopped onion and saute.
Drain off bacon grease.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Chop in pan; simmer and add beans after draining off liquid, to tomato mixture.
Stir gently; let simmer until juice is like a thin paste.
Add sugar last; stir in.
Taste and add more, if you like a sweeter taste.
Simmer and stir gently and often, because it could scorch as the juice thickens.
Allow at least 2 hours to make this dish.

title: pork chops 'n stuffing
directions: Mix soup and water.
Pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: delicious millet
directions: Combine the millet, water and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer.
Just before serving, stir in coconut, almonds and dates.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tortilla bites
directions: Mix together all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread mixture on tortillas.
Roll tortillas tightly, individually and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice into bite size pieces.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add grated cheese.
Combine dry ingredients; add to the cheese in 3 additions.
Mix well after each addition.
Make straws with cookie press.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Carefully remove to cool.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix together dates, soda and boiling water; let ingredients stand until cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together, then add date mixture.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour in tall pork and bean cans or small bread pans which have been greased and floured. Remove from cans while still warm.

title: shrimp cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, carrots and onion.
Chop bell pepper; add lemon juice and seasonings.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten; then add shrimp and mix.
Blend well.

title: slow cooker cranberry pork
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown roast in oil on all sides over medium-high heat. Transfer to a 5-quart slow cooker. Combine the cranberry sauce, sugar, cranberry juice, mustard, pepper and cloves. Pour over roast. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until a meat thermometer reads 160°. Remove roast and keep warm.

title: sugar cut outs
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream margarine and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Work flour into creamed mixture.
Wrap dough in foil or plastic and chill until firm.
Roll dough on floured board 1/4 at a time about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in desired shapes and bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes until golden on edges.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.
Decorate as desired.
(I use Jiffy icing.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix squash, sugar and eggs well.
Add oil and sifted dry ingredients.
Add lemon juice and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: carrot salad
directions: Partly cook carrots; drain and mix all vegetables together. Make sauce of sugar, tomato soup, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce; mix well and pour over vegetables.
Mix well; refrigerate.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute the ham and green onions until onions are tender.
Add eggs and cook over medium-high heat, stirring, to form large, soft curds.
When eggs are set, stir in mushrooms and Cheese Sauce.
Spoon eggs into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Combine 1/2 stick melted butter with the crumbs. Mix well.
Sprinkle evenly over egg mixture.
Cover and chill overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 12.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: baked eggs
directions: Scramble eggs with butter, milk, seasoning, onion and mushrooms.
Prepare sausages or bacon in separate skillet.
Layer in pan the eggs, soup, meat and cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 50 minutes.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly over salami.
Fold and serve. Presto!

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple slices, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Cut pineapple slices into quarters.
Set pineapple and juice aside.

title: double layer fudge
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add syrup and cream.
Cook to soft ball (firm) stage.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: roast beef
directions: Salt and pepper roast; put roast in pan with 1 cup water. Cover and bake at 350°.
Cook until all water is evaporated.
Turn and add 1 cup water.
Let cook 30 minutes more.
Turn fire out. Use brown gravy in bottom of pan to go over rice.

title: butter buds baked apples
directions: Combine ingredients and sprinkle in apple cavity.
Put in deep dish. Cover with Saran Wrap, making holes for steam to escape. Microwave 12 minutes on High, turning 1/4 turn every 3 minutes or bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: frozen salad supreme(yield:  12;  ring mold)
directions: Beat cream cheese with next 2 ingredients in mixer bowl until smooth.
Add fruit.
Whip the cream in mixer bowl until soft peaks form.
Fold into salad gently.
Spoon into mold.
Freeze until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter; pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: george washington pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in a slow 325° oven until a rich brown, about 45 minutes.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Rinse under cold water and drain.
In large bowl, combine wild rice, long grain rice, broccoli, celery, olives and green onions.
Combine vinegar, oil, garlic, salt and pepper for dressing.
Pour dressing over rice mixture.
Toss gently together.
Cover and chill 6 hours or overnight.
Before serving, add tomatoes.
Toss gently.
Makes 12 servings.

title: miniature open-faced reuben sandwiches
directions: Arrange bread slices on cookie sheets and toast under broiler. Remove from under broiler.
Place 1/2 strip corned beef on each slice.
Top with sauerkraut, cheese and sandwich spread (about 1 teaspoon). Return to broiler until cheese has started to melt. Remove and serve immediately.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Saute onion in margarine, add flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Stir in milk and 3/4 of cheese until cheese melts.
Pour in baking dish; add sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Melt margarine; add to crumbs and mix.
Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: lime-strawberry salad
directions: Then prepare a 3 ounce package of strawberry jello and pour over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: peanut butter play doh
directions: Mix in bowl with wooden spoon or clean hands.
More dry milk may be added to create a model consistency.

title: banana oat bran loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Combine bananas, sugar, oil, egg whites and milk; mix well.
Add combined flour, oat bran, baking powder and baking soda; mix until moistened.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
One sixteenth of loaf contains 130 calories and 4 grams fat.

title: fruit salad
directions: Do not drain fruits. Combine all fruits and sprinkle dry instant pudding over it. Stir to mix well. Will keep in the refrigerator 10 days.

title: dishcloth
directions: Cast on 4 stiches.
Knit 2 rows:
K2, yarn over, knit to end of row.
Continue this until you have 43 stitches.
Then decrease by K1, K2 together, yarn over, K2 together.
Knit to end of row. Continue until 4 stitches remain.
Knit 2 rows.
Bind off.

title: split pea vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine peas, water, allspice, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour. Stir in potatoes, carrots, onions, ham and cabbage.
Return to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients together. Add nuts. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes. When slightly cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini in salted water until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes; drain.
Melt 4 tablespoons margarine and saute onion until tender.
Remove from heat and add soup and sour cream.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups stuffing mix, then zucchini.
Put in casserole; add rest of stuffing mix over top.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine; spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: "good stuff" dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and spread it on crust.
Dot with instant pudding.
Put on top cheese mixture and top with more Cool Whip.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Fold in sour cream mixture, add banana pulp.
Stir and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: super nachos
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread and layer the ingredients (except sour cream).
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread sour cream on top and cook 5 minutes more.
Serve with taco chips or Doritos chips.
Makes lots.
Can be used as a main dish or an appetizer. Onions and 1/4 cup ripe olives can also be sprinkled on top after cooking.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: In medium size bowl sift flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add 3/4 cup of sugar and butter.
Mix dry ingredients.
Pour in milk and vanilla.
Set aside.
Next, mix in 8-inch pan the remaining 3/4 cup sugar, 5 tablespoons cocoa and boiling water.
Mix well.
Spoon batter mixture into syrup mixture.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 40 minutes.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: Fry beef and onion; drain off fat.
Fix instant potatoes. Boil potatoes; mash and add butter, salt and pepper as needed or to your liking.
Put meat in a casserole dish.
Pour potatoes on top.
Put grated cheese on top of potatoes to your liking.
Heat to melt cheese.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix together soup, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Pour over pork chops and bake, covered, 2 hours at 350°.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle parsley on wax paper or foil.
Roll up together.
Serve with round crackers.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix all thoroughly using only 1/4 cup of the tomato soup. Shape into small meatballs.
Place in pot.
Mix remaining soup, 1/2 cup water and 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer 35 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Put lamb in pot with real half peaches over it.
Pour 2 cups water, 2 cups peach wine, parsley, onions and flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with juices after 30 minutes.
Cover pot.

title: hamburg quiche
directions: Brown ground beef; drain excess grease and set ground beef aside.
Mix together mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch.
