Add to ground beef and then add cheese and onion.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake at 325° until top is brown and knife inserted in clean, approximately 1 hour.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Saute in butter the green pepper, garlic and onion.
Add diced, ripe tomatoes and chilies.
Mix thoroughly.
While this mixture is cooking slowly, grate cheese and melt in top of double boiler.
When melted, add the other ingredients to the cheese and blend well.
Serve in a chafing dish or in a preheated bowl with chips or crackers for dipping.

title: fluffy dinner rolls
directions: Soak
yeast in 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 cup warm water. Beat together 3 cups hot water, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup margarine, eggs, salt
and
flour to make soft dough.
When cool enough, add yeast. Stir in flour, beating as you continue.
When firm enough, turn out on floured board and knead, adding flour to a soft
dough. Let
rise in warm place.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
(Use half recipe if you wish.)

title: winner beef stew casserole
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook and stir meat and onions in oil over medium heat until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Pour off oil.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to mushroom liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir mushrooms and liquid into meat.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 2 hours.
Peel and thinly slice potatoes, cook for 10 minutes.
Pour meat mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Put potatoes over meat.
Combine soup, milk and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cracker crumbs if desired. Bake, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in blender for 4 to 5 minutes. Put in the remaining ingredients (vegetables).
Stir with a spoon and let set overnight in refrigerator; next day, remove the added vegetables and pour dressing into a jar.
Cover.
Can be kept in refrigerator for weeks.
Shake before using.

title: cauliflower souffle
directions: Cook and drain cauliflower.
Make white sauce with flour, milk and margarine. Cook until thick.
Add salt, pepper and bread crumbs. Set aside.

title: peach cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in flour and cinnamon.
Roll or pat to 1/2 inch thick to fit bottom of 6 1/2 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup, water and cornstarch until thick, the add raspberry flavored gelatin.
Into the prepared pie crust, place raspberries.
Pour the thickened glaze over the berries. Chill well.
Serve topped with lots of whipped cream.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add sugar.
Stir in cooled, melted butter.
Add beaten egg.
Stir in 2 cups flour and beat well.
Add remaining flour.
Keep dough in airtight bowl in refrigerator.

title: super chocolate cake
directions: Melt the chocolate in a double boiler in the cup of hot water. Bring to a boil.
Mix the chocolate and melted butter.
Sift the flour, sugar and salt.
Pour the chocolate and butter all at once into the dry ingredients and blend well.
Add buttermilk and soda and mix well.
Then add the eggs and vanilla.
Bake in a 350° oven for almost 30 minutes.
While the cake is in the oven, prepare the frosting.
Frost while warm.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg, then coconut, oatmeal and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Bake for 8 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugars and butter well.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Put 1/2 batter in pan.
Sprinkle 2 cups sliced rhubarb (raw) on top.
Cover with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain well.
Place all vegetables in crock-pot cooker.
Place beef on top.
Combine undrained tomatoes, barley, parsley, bouillon granules and salt.
Pour over meat.
Add water.
Do not stir.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: baked chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the chicken wings.
Stir until the sugar dissolves.
Marinate chicken wings in the mixture overnight.
Drain off mixture and bake wings at 350° for about 45 minutes.
If you like them crispier, broil for a minute after baking.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse peas; place in pan.
Add water, ham bone or hocks, onion, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.
Remove ham bone or hocks; remove and chop meat.
Discard bones.
Return meat to soup. Add carrot and celery.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Stir bacon, light cream and butter into soup; heat through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing mix by package directions.
Mix beef with milk.
Form 5 flat circles on waxed paper.
Spoon 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each circle.
Draw edges over stuffing and seal. Place in casserole dish.
Mix soup, Worcestershire sauce and catsup and heat until bubbly.
Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Dissolve jello with water and juice and chill until partially set.
Add fruit mixture and chill until firm.

title: vegetable-barley soup
directions: In cooking pot, heat 2 tablespoons salad oil; add onion.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add beef broth, basil, Italian seasonings, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Simmer, partially covered, 30 minutes. Add barley.
Simmer 30 minutes or until barley is tender.
Add tomatoes and vegetables.
Return to boiling.
Simmer until vegetables have cooked.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken toque (au grapes)
directions: Halve the grapes.
Place raw chicken in a large, shallow dish. Sprinkle grapes, onion and red peppers over chicken.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils; cook and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into container. Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups of syrup.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well
the
sugar,
flour,
cocoa and boiling water. Cook in	double	boiler	until thick. Remove from heat and add butter, 3
egg
yolks
and	milk.
Cook until thick. Pour into baked pie shell. Beat the egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff. Pour
over	chocolate
mixture
and bake in oven until browned.

title: holiday salad
directions: Put cottage cheese into bowl.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over it and stir.
Add drained fruit.
Fold into whipped topping.
Place in fancy bowl.
Easy.

title: never fail pecan pie
directions: Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until custard is firm.
Let cool.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: sour cream and raisin pie
directions: Mix flour and salt. Cut in shortening until pieces are pea size. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the cold water over the mixture and blend together. Continue with the rest of the water, one tablespoon at a time. Form dough into a ball. Roll out into a 12-inch diameter circle. Put into pie plate and prick the bottom of the shell with a fork. Line pastry with a double thickness of foil. Bake in a 450° oven for 8 minutes. Remove foil. Bake 5 to 6 minutes more or until golden. Cool on a wire rack.

title: shell's casserole
directions: Turn conventional oven to 400°.
Boil shells and brown ground beef.
Next, mix ground beef, shells, onion and tomato sauce together.
Put half of the mixture in a pan.
Put 3 slices of cheese on it.
Put the rest on top of the cheese.
Put the rest of the cheese on top.
Put it in the oven for about 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: whole wheat carrot and banana bread
directions: Makes 2 (7 1/2 x 3 3/4-inch) loaves or 1 large loaf.

title: scooby doo punch
directions: Mix together and chill before serving. Enjoy!

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix yeast in lukewarm water; set aside.
Stir Crisco and boiling water.
Let cool to lukewarm; then add yeast.
Add rest of ingredients except butter.
Mix well.
Let rise to double in size (approximately 1 to 2 hours).
Knead well.
Roll out flat and cut into strips (approximately 1 x 2-inch).
Dip strips into butter and layer in 2 Bundt pans.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 2 Bundt pans of bread.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Cream above ingredients together.
Spread in pie plate.
Top with sprinkles of more parmesan cheese and some chives.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: baked salmon
directions: Place salmon in shallow baking dish.
Mix other ingredients to spread on top of salmon.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until slightly brown.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased pan.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° until heated through.
Keep warm over candle, etc.
Serve with shrimp flavored rice crunch crackers.

title: corn salad
directions: Boil last six ingredients together.
Pour over corn.
Put in refrigerator.
Very good with vegetables.

title: perfect peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches on bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sift together dry ingredients; add egg, tossing with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese-crab casserole
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain and rinse.
In a medium casserole dish, mix crab and cheese.
Add milk.
Bake at 350° until heated through. Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and place in small amount of boiling salted water.
Cover pan tightly and boil 15 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Remove from water.
Melt brown sugar and margarine in skillet.
Cook over low heat, turning occasionally, until carrots are well glazed.

title: papier-mache paste(for the kids on a rainy day)
directions: Mix flour and water well; let stand until flour is dissolved, about 20 minutes.
Cook over low heat until transparent.
Stir constantly.
Remove from fire and place in covered jar.
Add a few drops of oil of cloves.
Paste may be kept in refrigerator several days.
Cover a bowl with vaseline.
Dip strips of paper in paste and lay crisscross several times.
Let dry.
Sandpaper and paint.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Pour crushed pineapple on top.
Spread dry cake mix over pineapple. Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle on coconut and then nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: minzola minzetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and salt.
Drain fat.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add Cheddar cheese and tomato soup to hamburger mixture.
Add noodles; stir until well coated.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Pour soup in pan.
Heat.
Mix gelatine with 1/4 cup water to make paste.
Add to soup.
Stir well.
Put in cream cheese and stir until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in bowl or mold. Tastes better if made ahead.
Refrigerate.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix water and cocoa; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 3 cake pans or 1 oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried crispy oven chicken
directions: Skin the chicken.
Use 1/4 cup oil for pan.
Mix other 5 ingredients.
Coat chicken and bake.

title: french onion soup
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onions and sugar for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour until well blended with onions and the pan juices.
Add water, wine and beef broth.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Simmer 10 minutes. Cut 4 (1-inch thick) slices of bread.
Toast in oven.
Ladle soup into oven-safe bowls and place 1 slice of bread on top.
Lay Swiss over bread slice.
Place soup bowls on jelly roll pan for easier handling.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Melt jello in hot water and let cool.
Let cream cheese soften.
Mix cream cheese, pineapple and pecans.
Add jello to cream cheese mixture.
Put in refrigerator until thick but
not firm.
Whip the cream.
Add to jello and let set in refrigerator.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle the nuts and coconut on bottom of lightly greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on back of box, then pour over nuts and coconut.
Set aside.

title: norwegian meatballs
directions: Combine 1/2 cup milk, bread crumbs, egg, onion and seasonings; let stand until crumbs absorb milk.
Add meat; stir only until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown on all sides in small amount of vegetable oil.
Arrange meatballs in 2-quart casserole.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Put batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook and cool.

title: don't peek chicken
directions: Combine soups and water with rice and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Lay chicken parts on top of rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle onion soup over top.
Cover with foil and bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Don't peek during the cooking period.

title: skillet banana in orange juice
directions: Slice banana into a sherbet dish.
Pour the orange juice over the slices and place the dish in the refrigerator to chill. Contains 80 calories.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat, saute vegetables in butter with the garlic.
Add rest of ingredients
(except potatoes).
Simmer to blend flavors, then put into casserole dish.
Cover top of mixture with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until potatoes are browned.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Cook rice separately and cool.
Combine rice, chicken, carrots, raisins and onion.
In a small bowl or jar, combine oil, vinegar, mustard, garlic, salt and Tabasco sauce. Mix well.
Pour over rice mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce.
Sprinkle with toasted macadamia nuts.

title: snak oyster crax
directions: Put crackers in a large paper bag.
Mix ingredients and pour over crackers.
Shake well.
Spread crackers on foil for about 20 minutes.
Store in tight bowl.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except ketchup.
Mix well.
Place in loaf pan.
Spread ketchup over the top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour in conventional oven.
Or microwave on High for approximately 18 minutes, rotating pan halfway through cooking time.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate layered bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk in saucepan.
Melt over low heat.
Stir in walnuts and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract; set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients with fork; mixture will be coarse (crumbs).
Press half of the crumb mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread chocolate mixture over this, then sprinkle the remaining crumb mixture over the top of the chocolate filling.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: daddy's pigs
directions: Mix ground beef and rice.
Add onions and bell peppers.
Mix. Cut heart out of cabbage.
Put cabbage in kettle and fill 1/2 way with water.
Steam until leaves are wilted.
Remove cabbage and remove leaves.
Roll a piece of hamburger mixture into a large meatball.
Shape and put in base of unfolded cabbage leaf.
Fold leaf sides in and roll up.
Place in large pot. Continue with rest of leaves and mixture, placing a pat of butter in and around each layer.
Fill pot with 3/4 water.
Cook 2 hours.
Salt to taste.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs and mix together sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add to eggs.
Add oleo and mix well.
Then add vannila and lemon juice, pineapple and coconut.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and reduce to 300° and bake until done.

title: carnation famous fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square baking dish with foil.
Combine sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt in medium, heavy-duty saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil, stirring constantly for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla extract.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into prepared baking pan; refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm. Lift from pan; remove foil.
Cut into pieces.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Put in blender until thoroughly mixed together.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Form meatballs, brown in 1/4 cup oil.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together and cover with 2 cups crumbled Ritz crackers and 1 stick margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
For first 20 minutes, cover with foil.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix together cream cheese, flour, butter and margarine.
Form ball the size of walnuts.
Press into greased small muffin forms. Mix brown sugar, egg and pecans.
Put mixture into dough shells. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans.
Makes 24 tarts.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cover pizza pan with cookie dough.
Bake at 375° until light brown; cool.
Drain fruit.
Beat sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Spread mixture over crust.
Place fruit over cheese mixture.
Spread coconut over entire pizza.
Store in refrigerator.

title: puffed strawberry omelette
directions: Sprinkle the strawberries with 1 tablespoon of the sugar and the orange juice; set aside for half an hour.
Beat the egg yolks for about 3 minutes while slowly adding the remaining sugar and the vanilla.
They will be quite thick.
Beat the whites with the salt until they stand in soft peaks.
Fold them gently into the yolks.

title: pea sausage
directions: Cream the peas, then add flour and sausage.
Mix well. Dip by spoonfuls. Fry in oil.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: On large platter, spread bean dip; top with chopped olives, then top with sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mixture. Cover with seeded and chopped tomatoes; sprinkle with chopped onions and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oats, flour, brown sugar and butter until creamy.
Place 1/2 mixture into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Cover with cranberries. Top with balance of crumb mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Top with Cool Whip.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: glazed carrots(microwave)
directions: Place carrots and water in casserole; cover with tight lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 100% for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Allow to stand 5 minutes, then drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in a cup and microwave on High for 2 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Pour over carrots and cover.
Microwave for 1 to 2 minutes, until heated through on High.
Serves 2 or 3 persons.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion; steam for 12 to 15 minutes and drain. Add mushroom soup, water and sour cream; mix well.
In separate bowl, melt margarine; mix in seasoning packet from dressing.
Then mix bread crumb packet.
Place half of bread crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour squash mixture over crumbs. Sprinkle with remaining half of crumb mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Wait for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Tear the center out of the rye bread.
Place dip in the center and serve with pieces of rye around the bread.

title: chili
directions: In a large Dutch oven or soup kettle, brown beef until no longer pink.
Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic. Continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Add all remaining ingredients, except last two (macaroni and kidney beans).
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, adding macaroni for last half hour of cooking time.
Stir in the beans and heat through.
Yields 12 servings.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake frozen pie shells 5 to 7 minutes.
Place tomatoes in bottom of pie shell.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: best ever pecan pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks until light and thick.
Mix sugar and spices.
Add to egg yolks.
Add pecans, raisins and butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold gently into mixture (do not beat).
Add vinegar as you fold.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then reduce to 350°.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with unsweetened whipped cream if you wish. (I serve mine without the whipped cream.)

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Melt 1/2 cup butter in oblong pan, 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle 1 cup brown sugar (packed) evenly over butter.
Arrange 6 drained pineapple rings over sugar. Decorate with walnut halves and maraschino cherries.
Make cake batter as directed.
Pour over fruit in pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Invert at once onto serving plate.

title: curried pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic; cook, stirring frequently for 2-3 minutes or until tender. Stir in curry, salt, and pepper; cook 1 minute. Add broth and pumpkin; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring occasionally, for 15-20 minutes. Transfer mixture to food processor or blender (in batches, if necessary); cover. Blend until smooth. Serve warm. Holds well in crockpot set on low.

title: cranberry-apple crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine apples, cranberries, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and place on top of apple mixture.
Bake for about 1 hour until bubbly and slightly brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a large pot.
Cover with water and simmer until tender.
While this cooks, make egg balls by mixing 1 teaspoon of salt with egg; add flour gradually until dough is stiff enough to handle (you may not need all the flour). Roll dough into marble size balls.
When vegetables are tender, add egg balls and more water, if needed, to cover.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add 1 quart of milk and heat to the boiling point but do not boil.
Season to taste and sprinkle each serving with minced chives.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: yummy cake
directions: Mix fruit and turn into oblong greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle the package of cake mix over the fruit. Cut up butter over the top and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Cream sugar and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Mix all ingredients together, Alternately add dry ingredients and water to sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: green congealed salad
directions: Bring pineapple in juice to boil. Add lemon and lime jello. Add other ingredients. Pour into 9 x 9-inch dish and place in refrigerator. When congealed, cut in squares. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: baked scallops
directions: Wash and drain scallops.
Melt margarine.
Toss scallops in melted margarine, bread crumbs and garlic powder.
Place in greased baking dish.
Drizzle wine over top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Mix sugar and water in an iron pan and cook until sugar melts. Add peanuts and continue cooking until sugar coats nuts.
Stir while cooking.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir often.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers, in a medium mixing bowl; mix well. Refrigerate for several hours to allow flavors to blend. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: kissy cookies
directions: Cut cookie dough into 13 even slices; cut each slice into quarters.
Place paper baking cups into miniature (1 3/4-inch) muffin pans.
Place 1 dough quarter into each cup.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes, or until lightly browned (do not overbake).
Remove from oven.
Immediately press a chocolate drop into center of each cookie.
Let cool in pan.
Store in airtight containers.
Yields 52 cookies.

title: easy cherry tarts
directions: Divide pie filling among the crusts.
Top with whipped topping and chocolate sprinkles; chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: quick black bean mexican soup
directions: Pour olive oil into soup pot and saute onion for 2 minutes over medium heat. Add garlic, jalapeno and tomatoes sauteing for another 2 minutes. Add beans with juice, water and bouillon and spices.
Simmer.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: In 10-inch greased pie plate, mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese.
In blender or by hand mixer, beat eggs, milk and Bisquick.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: candy cane and wreath cookies
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and flavorings.
Combine flour and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Set aside half of the dough.
Divide remaining half into 2 parts.
Tint one part green and the other red with food color or paste.
Keep dough chilled for easy handling.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: First, mix together the first three ingredients and form into small balls.
Brown balls in oil.
Next, mix the next 3 ingredients and pour over balls.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: coconut krispie balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and add dates.
Cook over low heat until dates dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour over Rice Krispies and shape into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: patti salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; add to sour cream and marshmallows. Refrigerate.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks.
Fold in pecans. Pour butter in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Spread pecan mixture over.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes; cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Remove crust from bread and crumble the crust.
Make donuts and holes from bread slices.
In 13 x 9-inch buttered pan layer crumbs, ham and Cheddar cheese.
Then place donuts and holes of bread on top. Pour liquid over top and refrigerate for 5 hours or overnight. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: favorite icebox cookies
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Cream shortening and sugar gradually and cream together thoroughly.
Add eggs, coconut, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Add flour gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Shape each part in 1 1/2-inch diameter and roll in wax paper.
Chill overnight or until firm enough to slice in 1/8-inch slices.
Bake at 425°.

title: custard corn pudding
directions: Start heating oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients; pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set in pan of warm water. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: omelet casserole
directions: Remove bread crusts.
Make 8 (buttered on outside) ham and cheese sandwiches.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings and pour over sandwiches.
Refrigerate overnight.
In morning, cover with 1 1/2 cups crushed cornflakes mixed with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add water, then brown sugar.
Mix in nuts and coconut.
Spread evenly in pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on package, then pour over mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes so topping will begin to set.
Turn out onto cookie sheet.

title: crabmeat mold
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Save juice.
Add water to juice to make 3 tablespoons.
Dissolve gelatin in this.
Heat undiluted soup.
Cut up cream cheese and add to soup along with gelatin mixture. Remove from heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Beat smooth. Add rest of ingredients and blend well.
Put into a 4-cup mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Cook figs, sugar and water for 1 or 2 minutes and then mash. Add gelatin and cook 3 minutes more.
Put in jars while hot and seal.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine soup mix and rice in a 1-3/4 quart shallow casserole dish.
Add boiling water, stirring until soup mix is dissolved. Set aside.
Combine sausage, celery, pepper and onion in skillet and cook until browned.
Drain.
Add meat mixture, pimento and water chestnuts to soup and stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Lightly grease large angel food cake pan.
Beat until smooth first 8 ingredients.
Mix next 3 ingredients together in separate bowl.
Pour 1/2 batter in pan.
Place layer of apples over batter. Pour rest of batter in pan.
Put remaining apples on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: chocolate cream nectar
directions: Melt chocolate in saucepan over low heat.
Add coffee and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add sugar and water and cook 5 minutes.
Chill.
Add vanilla.

title: danish pastry
directions: Heat the water and margarine and boil until rolling.
Take off stove.
Add flour all at once and mix well. Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Mix in the almond extract.
Spread mixture evenly over the top of the crust mixture. Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In heavy 4-quart kettle, melt 1 tablespoon margarine and saute yellow onion and garlic for 2 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth. Add broccoli florets, carrots, celery and green onion.
Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat to simmer.
Cover, leaving cover just slightly ajar to prevent broccoli from turning olive drab in color.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Sift 4 cups of thoughtfulness with innumerable smiles and dash of salt.
Add several brimming cups of kindness, 7 tablespoons of the oil of forgiveness and
a good cup of cheerfulness; mix well with care.
Bake continuously in the warmth of God's love.
Serve abundant portions, covered with smiles, to all you meet.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Place all ingredients in iron skillet and cook on top of stove until liquid is absorbed in peanuts.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Salt real well.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Stir and salt again.
Cook 15 minutes longer.
Cool and store.

title: jello candy
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup, water and salt to 250°.
Beat egg whites well.
Add Jell-O and beat well.
Pour syrup slowly into egg white and Jell-O mixture.
Beat until stiff.
Spoon on wax paper.

title: sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil on stove milk and butter until melted.
Mix dry ingredients together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and sugar together until sugar is dissolved. Alternate dry ingredients and milk while still beating good.
Add flavoring.
Use a Bundt pan or angel food pan, greased and floured.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in oil.
Add other ingredients and bring to boil. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand about 5 to 10 minutes, then fluff rice.

title: cherry jello
directions: Heat pie filling to boil.
Add cherry jell-o.
Stir until dissolved.
Remove from stove.
Add coca-cola, pineapple.
Stir well.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: pasta salad and raisins
directions: Stir together the first 8 ingredients to serve.
Toss avocado and banana with it.
Pineapple juice may be added to prevent darkening.
Add to salad along with dressing.
Serve on a bed of torn lettuce or spinach leaves.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: two minute fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk in a 1 1/2-quart glass bowl.
Place 1 stick butter on top; cook in microwave for 2 minutes on High (10) power.
Stir well.
Butter will melt as you stir.
Fold in nuts and marshmallows (optional).
Pour into buttered pan to cool.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Stir by hand.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add pineapple, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch oiled pan.

title: fish bake
directions: Wash fish and place in a baking dish.
Pour all ingredients over fish and bake covered for 15 minutes at 350° or until fish is flaky.

title: texas fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into almost 1/2-inch thick slices.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and seasoning salt in one bowl.
Mix eggs and milk in another bowl.
Dip each tomato slice into the milk mixture, then into the flour, back to the milk and then to the flour again, coating well.

title: pickled cherry hot peppers
directions: Wash peppers and cut into quarters.
Pack tightly in jar. Fill jar 2/3 with white vinegar.
Fill remainder with water to 3/4-inch from top. Top off with olive oil.
Put lids on tightly. Turn upside down on towel on countertop.
Turn over and tighten lids each day for 6 days. Store in cool, dark place.

title: quick and easy tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package until done.
Drain.
While noodles cook, mix rest of ingredients except cheese together.
Add drained noodles to mixture. Pour into a large casserole dish.
Top with cheese (amount of your choice).
Cover and microwave until cheese melts and mixture is piping hot (about 7 minutes).
Can bake in oven at 350°, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes instead of microwaving.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut slice from top of each.
Scoop out insides; mash well with fork or potato masher.
Add butter, sour cream, salt, pepper, milk, onion and chives.
Beat until fluffy. Pile lightly into shells.
Sprinkle tops with grated cheese.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes to brown lightly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well and store in container.
To serve, mix 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly in a medium size bowl.
Stir in sugar, butter, flour and pineapple.
Stir in bread cubes.
Pour into a greased
1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 1 hour.
This is good served with ham.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix peas in saucepan with soup (heat until hot, not boiling). Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter until crumbly.
Pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry marshmallow cream
directions: Mix together strawberries, pineapple and sugar in large bowl. Fold marshmallows into whipped cream.
Fold whipped cream mixture into strawberry mixture.
Chill until serving time.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, pecans and butter. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: crock-pot chicken and mushrooms
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot and sprinkle with dry salad dressing mix.
Set on low for 6 hours.
Later add soup, water, onion, sour cream and mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly and allow to heat on low for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.
tags: Italian Good Seasons salad dressing mix

title: meal in a dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Slice a layer of potatoes into buttered casserole, then a layer of meat and onion mixture, peas, soup, salt and pepper.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Cover casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine shortening and sugar; cream well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients, mix well.
Add pecans, dates and chopped cherries; mix well.
Shape into ball using about a tablespoonful for each cookie.
Roll each ball of dough in cornflakes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Top each cookie with 1/4 of a cherry.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not stack or store until cold.

title: old-fashioned chicken 'n noodles
directions: In a large saucepan, place chicken, water, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour until chicken is tender; remove chicken.
Remove skin and bones from chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Measure broth, adding enough hot water to make 6 cups liquid; return to pan.
Add celery, carrots, onion and parsley.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender.
Heat to boiling.
Add noodles; boil, uncovered, 5 to 7 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Add mushrooms; heat thoroughly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: refreshing iced tea punch
directions: In a 5 gallon drink cooler, dissolve tea.
Mix with 3 gallons water.
Add orange juice and 2 blocks of ice.

title: orange tea
directions: Steep tea; add sugar and frozen juices.
Stir until well dissolved.
Add enough water to make 1 gallon.
Will keep in refrigerator for a few days.

title: oatmeal banana bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix, oats and nuts; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; stir in bananas and milk.
Add dry ingredients all at once, stirring until moistened.
Turn into greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan; cool.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add carrots, cottage cheese and pineapple.
Chill and serve.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: red and white salad
directions: Mix lemon jello and boiling water.
While hot, add cream cheese, marshmallows and crushed pineapple.
When this begins to set, add the mayonnaise and Cool Whip.
Fold in and let set. Sprinkle red jello over top.
Be sure jello is cooled, but not set, before pouring over white mixture.

title: green pea salad
directions: Layer all ingredients as given.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Put crumbled bacon on just before serving.

title: tasty bean dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend in beans and seasonings.
Chill and serve with chips or crackers.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well; add eggs. Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with yogurt. Stir in pears and vanilla. Pour into greased 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Mix cracker crumbs with butter. Spread 1/3 crumbs in a greased baking dish, 10 x 6 x 7 1/2. Arrange over crumbs 1 small can of drained oysters, salt and pepper, then crumbs and other can of oysters, then rest of crumbs. Add 2/3 cup of liquid (oyster liquid and milk). Bake 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas.
Mix dry ingredients and add to banana mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Slice and dice all the vegetables, then combine sour cream, mayo and Hidden Valley Original and pour over vegetables.
Let set for one hour in refrigerator.

title: uncle bill's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on low in a crock-pot all day. Enjoy!

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry mixture; beat well.
Add rest of flour to make stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 pans, 8 1/2 x 4-inch, that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover; let rise for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.
To serve:
Slice and toast.

title: crab au gratin(or convert to crabmeat quiche)
directions: Saute green onions and parsley in butter until soft. Remove from heat and stir in flour, salt and pepper, gradually stir in milk. Stir over low heat until thickened. Remove from heat and add sherry, gently fold in crabmeat. Place in casserole dish, sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried puff squares(spanish name:  hojuelas)
directions: Mix the margarine and flour with a fork.
Add salt, sugar, juice and water; blend.
Roll the dough out and fold it in half. Repeat this operation 2 more times and place in the refrigerator until chilled.
Roll out very thin and cut into diagonal strips. Make a slit in the center of each one.
Deep fry in hot cooking oil until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle sugar generously over the squares.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: aunt bill's microwave candy
directions: Cook in casserole which holds 3 times the amount of ingredients or it will boil over.
Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and oleo. Cover with plastic wrap.
Punch holes in wrap.
Microwave on Roast (70%) for 15 minutes.
Stir and return to the microwave and continue cooking on Roast (70%) for 13 to 15 minutes until soft ball forms in cold water (236° on candy thermometer).
Don't put thermometer in microwave.
Add vanilla and beat with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Watch closely.
Stir in pecans and pour into buttered 11 x 17-inch dish.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients in processor until smooth.
Add pepper and flaked smoked salmon.
Process gently.
Transfer to bowl.
Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors.

title: chicken with wild rice
directions: Cook chicken in water, wine, salt, curry, onion and celery for 1 hour.
Strain and reserve juice.
Debone chicken.
Saute mushrooms in butter. Cook rice according to box, using reserved juice plus water as needed.
Mix chicken, rice and mushrooms together. Add sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour into 3-quart baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: corn muffin casserole
directions: Melt margarine, saute green pepper and onions until tender (if not using green pepper and substituting instant onion), add melted margarine and instant onion to combined corn, eggs and muffin mix. Mix well and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until firm and set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: raisin water cake
directions: Boil seedless raisins about 20 minutes.
Drain and save 3/4 cup raisin water.
Mix sugar, shortening, egg, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; add 3/4 cup cooked raisin water.
Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to raisin water mixture.
Then add cooked raisins.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Use cone or Bundt pan.
Cool for 5 minutes in pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: To soften the cream cheese, let it sit, covered, at room temperature several hours or microwave on Low about 1 minute.
In a medium size mixing bowl, mix the lemon juice and cream cheese together.
Stir the shrimp and green onion into the cream cheese. Add the mayonnaise and stir in the hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Turn the mixture into a serving dish and chill.
This dish is a lot better if it is made a day or several hours ahead.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix and boil everything but strawberries and food coloring until clear and very thick.
Cool completely.
Add to the mixture the quart of strawberries and food coloring.
Pour into a large baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip before serving.

title: strawberry, coconut and nut cake
directions: Bake cake ingredients in three layers at 350° until done.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, then mix together with other ingredients, except Tater Tots.
Pour mixture in casserole dish and top with Tater Tots.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: eggs souffle
directions: Place bread slices in bottom of greased Pyrex pan.
Melt cheese with butter; pour over bread.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over cheese mixture; let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: paw's favorite old fashion oatmeal cookies
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
Take only such that has been raised in a good moral atmosphere.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others keep them in hot water.
This only makes sour, hard and sometimes bitter.

Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste, then wrap them in a mantle for charity, keep them warm with a steady fire of steady devotion, and serve with three good meals a day.
When this is prepared, they will keep for years.

title: quick and easy grape-nuts pudding
directions: Cook rice and salt in water until cooked.
Rinse; set aside.

title: octoberfest ribs
directions: * If using Juniper berries or caraway seed, bury them evenly in the sauerkraut layer.

title: ice tea
directions: Let water come to boil.
Add tea.
Let draw five minutes. Strain and add sugar.
Serve 1 inch tea to 1 glass of water.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix cornflakes, nut and coconut.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff.
Add 1 cup sugar, 1/2 stick melted margarine, vanilla, lemon, nutmeg and mace; add to first mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet (do not run).
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes (do not brown).
Cool on cookie sheet.

title: barbecue sauce and spice(serves 1)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: salmon delight
directions: Spray 1 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick oil.
Set aside. Melt margarine; cook onions and green peppers until soft.
Drain and save salmon liquid.
Mix salmon, rice, onions and green peppers.
Add milk to salmon liquid to make 2/3 cup of liquid. Combine with soup and mix until blended.
Cover bottom of casserole with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Place one-half salmon mixture over crumbs evenly.
Cover with one-half soup mixture. Repeat salmon/soup layer and cover with remaining crumbs.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine and drizzle over crumbs.
Top with almonds. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes six 1-cup servings.

title: sally lunn hot bread
directions: Soak yeast in lukewarm water.
Beat eggs well, until light in color.
Add milk and butter (after milk has been heated to lukewarm temperature).
Add sugar, salt, yeast and flour.
Pour into large bowl and let double in size.
Beat well and pour into an oiled, angel food cake pan; allow 1 1/4 hours to rise.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together the cake mix, butter and pecans. Press into bottom of baking dish. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Spread apple pie filling on top. Sprinkle the cinnamon and sugar on top of filling. Mix together the egg and sour cream; spread on top and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: maple syrup
directions: Combine ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Cool at room temperature.
Store in refrigerator. Warm slightly before reusing.
Yield:
1 pint.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Use 9-inch unbaked pie shell.

title: peanut butter face
directions: Spread peanut butter on a piece of bread, then take two slices of your banana, lay on top of the bread for eyes, then take a raisin and place in the center of the banana slices, then take one more banana slice for the nose.
Then a slice of apple for the mouth.
Finally, take your coconut and place at the very top of the bread for hair.
Quick and easy for children to make a healthy snack.

title: sigrid's pistachio salad
directions: Do not drain pineapple.
Mix marshmallows, pineapple and pistachio pudding well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Let stand awhile, preferably overnight.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar in crust with fingers.
Pour cream in and keep mixing until smooth.
Pour butter on top and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lime fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving syrup.
In a saucepan, combine reserved fruit syrup, water and the lime gelatin.
Heat, stirring frequently, until gelatin is dissolved.
Gradually add hot gelatin mixture to cream cheese; beat with rotary beater until smooth. Chill until partially set (the consistency of unbeaten egg whites).
Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold drained fruit cocktail, walnuts and whipped cream into gelatin mixture. Pour into a 3 1/2-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix 1 heaping tablespoonful flour with sugar. Add eggs, cream and syrup. Mix in pecans, butter and vanilla. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chunk babka
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water.
Combine 4 cups of the flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cut 8 tablespoons of the butter into the flour.
Combine the yeast mixture with the yolks and sour cream and beat into flour until dough is smooth and starts to come away from the sides of the bowl.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten yolks, then boiling water, stirring as you pour.
Cook and stir until thick.
Cool before pouring into pie crust.
Make meringue out of 3 egg whites and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Cover pie with meringue and bake until brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients. Add powdered sugar and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip, reserving some for the top. Place in crust and chill.

title: coconut bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla, milk and rum.
Mix together bread and raisins and add to egg mixture.
Bake in 8 x 8 greased pan at 325 degrees until done - 1 to 1-1/2 hours, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, then spoon onto griddle and cook on low-medium heat.

title: low calorie spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until blended.
Store mixture in an airtight container.

title: sweet chunk pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Pour boiling water over; let stand overnight. Drain.
On four consecutive days, repeat the process.
Add fresh boiling water and drain.
On the fifth day, cut drained cucumbers into 1/4-inch slices.

title: green tomato pickle
directions: Prepare 3
quart
size canning jars. Core tomatoes, cut into 6 to
wedges and place in bowl. Cut onions into 1-inch cubes and bell peppers into 1-inch squares; add to bowl.
Cut carrots in half lengthwise, then cut carrots and celery into 1 1/2 inch lengths; add to bowl.
Mix vegetables thoroughly and set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and mix.
Chill, then it's ready to serve.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator for best results.

title: miss clara's chess pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and corn meal.
Add eggs and continue beating.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° until beginning to brown.
Reduce heat and bake at 250° until set.

title: microwave fillets amandine
directions: In a 2-cup measure, combine almonds and 2 Tbsp. butter.
Cook on HIGH 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
In a 7 1/2 x 12-inch utility dish, melt 3 Tbsp. butter on HIGH for 35 seconds.
Stir in lemon juice and add fish.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on HIGH for 5 minutes, depending on thickness of fillets.
Sprinkle with salt, garlic powder and almonds.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in oil until tender.
Add meat and cook until it loses its color.
Add chili powder and tomatoes. Cook 10 minutes over medium heat. Stir in rice and salt. Put in shallow baking dish. Add cheese on top.
Put under broiler until bubbly.

title: spicy mustard
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add just enough malt vinegar to make a dense, spreadable consistency.
Serve over slices of sharp Cheddar on a cracker.

title: oreo cookie torte
directions: Mix Oreos and melted oleo in oblong glass dish.
Then mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of last layer.
Mix 1 large chocolate pudding; spread on top of last layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Crumble 1 or 2 Oreo cookies on top.
Refrigerate.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all, cover and boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Let set 30 minutes.
Serve hot with orange slice.

title: monster oatmeal raisins
directions: Preheat oven to 325° with oven rack in center.
Spread oats on a baking sheet; toast 15 minutes, stirring frequently, until they are pale gold and smell deliciously nutty.
Cool.
Increase oven temperature to 350°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.

title: orange blossom cake
directions: Line bottom of a nonstick 9 x 5-inch loaf pan (or 8-inch round cake pan) with wax paper.
Using large bowl and electric beater, beat egg whites with cream of tartar, orange extract (or concentrate) and salt, if using, until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until thoroughly dissolved. In several portions, sprinkle flour over surface of beaten whites and fold in carefully with a rubber spatula.
Spoon mixture into the prepared pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Before baking, the cake will be very high and puffy; it will be level while baking.
Cook cake by inverting pan and resting edges on the edges of 2 other pans. When completely cool, loosen edges of cake with a spatula and remove from pan.

title: cheese-pineapple ball
directions: Soften cheese and stir in drained pineapple.
Add 1 1/4 cups pecans and	remaining
ingredients.
Chill.
Roll
into a ball, then roll in remaining pecans.

title: flavorful rice pilaf
directions: Put the water into a saucepan with the coriander or cilantro and bring to a boil.
At the same time, heat the oil in a flameproof casserole.
Add the rice to the oil until grains are just coated, then add the water to the casserole.
Cover and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes.
By then the water should be all absorbed into the rice.
During the baking, put the apple slices and cinnamon into the apple juice to soak.
When the rice is done, drain the apples and blend them and the raisins into the rice.
Add the chopped green onions at the very end.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, brown sugar and white sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and eggs.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 25 minutes in tube pan.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; add all except oats and chocolate chips and mix.
Add oats and chocolate chips.
Stir well and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 13 minutes at 350°.

title: special spinach salad(blender)
directions: Mix all ingredients in food blender except spinach.
Chill and serve over spinach.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine yeast, 3 cups flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. Heat milk and water to 120° to 130°.
Add to first ingredients, mix well, then add additional 2 cups of flour.
Pour into 2 glass bread pans that have been sprayed with pan and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle cornmeal on top and let rise in a warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake in microwave for 6 minutes, no longer, than 6 1/2 minutes. Let rest 5 minutes.
Eat fresh or toast.

title: chicken in herb wine sauce
directions: Combine garlic salt, flour, rosemary, thyme and basil.
Coat chicken with combined mixture.
Brown both sides of chicken in 5 tablespoons of butter in heavy skillet.
Add wine.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Saute onions and mushrooms in remaining butter and add to chicken.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes or until tender.
Serve sprinkled with parsley.

title: crumb crust
directions: Combine
together
crumbs
and	butter	into 9-inch pie plate. Press and cool.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add 1 teaspoon sugar.
In a bowl, cream sugar, lard and egg.
Add warm water; beat.
Add dissolved yeast; beat in flour and salt.
Let rise, then press down when doubled and roll out or put in refrigerator and make rolls as needed.

title: stir-n-drop lemon sugar cookie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs with a fork until blended.
Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon rind.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and stir into mixture.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a greased glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes just until a delicate brown.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: basque sangria
directions: Combine wine, orange juice and Cointreau in a large pitcher; stir gently.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Stir in club soda, lemon slices and orange slices just before serving. Serve over ice.

title: frozen pudding sandwiches
directions: Add milk gradually to peanut butter in deep narrow bottom bowl, blending until smooth.
Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer until well blended, about 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: tea tassies
directions: Let cheese and butter soften, then beat together and add flour.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape chilled dough into small balls (about 24 to 30).
Place one ball in each cup of ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.
Press ball in center and shape on bottom and sides of cups, forming a shell.

title: crab pate
directions: Heat soup in a medium saucepan over low heat; remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup, stirring well.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Chill in mold until firm.
Unmold and garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers. Yields about 4 cups.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix flour, milk, salt and pepper together.
Place cheese on top of macaroni, then pour 1/2 of sauce over it.
Put another layer of macaroni, then the rest of cheese and sauce.
Sprinkle a little plain breadcrumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: shrimp and crab gumbo
directions: In a medium
bowl,
combine
the onion, celery and bell pepper, then set aside.
In
a
small cup, mix all the seasonings well and set
aside.
Next,
you need to make your shrimp stock. Peel and
devein
shrimp.
Place shrimp shells and all the vegetable trimmings from the onion, celery and bell pepper in a 3 quart saucepan;
cover
with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer
about
35 minutes.
Strain and set the stock aside.

title: spaghetti sauce and meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot; simmer.

title: chocolate pie supreme
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and 1 cup of milk in medium mixing bowl.
Add puddings.
Mix thoroughly.
Gradually add rest of milk and vanilla.
Pour into a 10-inch baked pie shell.
Chill.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil until creamy.
Add zucchini.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; add to zucchini mixture.
Stir in cinnamon.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, tossing gently.
Add dressing.
Chill slightly before serving.

title: perfect meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until forms a soft peak, adding 6 tablespoons sugar gradually, then add cream of tartar and beat 1 minute longer.
Put on pie and bake in oven on 400°.

title: curry goat
directions: Place meat in a glass baking dish.
Season with 1 chopped onion, curry, thyme, pepper and salt.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove meat from refrigerator the next day.
Place meat in a large saucepan; cover with water.
Add oil.
Simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add remaining half chopped onion.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: tortiere(french canadian meat pie)
directions: Saute pork and beef with onion until meat is cooked.
Drain off fat.
Add mashed potatoes, herbs and seasonings.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells; cover with top crust and seal edges.
Make a few vent holes in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until crust is cooked.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix butter and herb stuffing mix together.
Place half of stuffing mix on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over stuffing mixture.
Pour other half of stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in lemon rind, lemon juice, egg yolks and milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 1 quart baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water (1 inch deep).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold, with or without whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: citrus baked pears
directions: Core pears and remove skin half way down.
Combine brown sugar, walnuts and butter.
Fill center of each pear with mixture. Place pears in 8-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over pears. Sprinkle with grated lemon and orange peel.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly. Press into pie plate and up on sides. Bake 8 minutes at 375°. This is the same as graham cracker crust.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well for several days.

title: mock chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add the diced celery, then the raw rice.

title: soy pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Add tenderloins.
They can marinate 5 minutes or overnight, depending on your schedule.
In a small pan, or in the microwave, toast sesame seeds until light brown.
Set aside.
Use a baking sheet with shallow sides to roast the pork.
Grease sheet lightly, then remove pork from soy sauce mixture and place on sheet.
Bake 20 minutes.
Pour remaining marinade over the tenderloin and continue baking another 5 minutes.
Remove pork from oven, slice thin slices on the diagonal and place on platter.
Pour the pan juices over the pork, sprinkle with sesame seeds and serve. Suggestion:
Serve with steamed rice and fresh asparagus.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Lightly grease pie plate.
Put broccoli, onion, pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs; salt and pepper and pour over vegetables.
Cook at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: california chicken enchiladas
directions: Put chicken breasts in baking dish.
Shake season salt (orange kind) on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
(This can be done ahead of time and refrigerated.)

title: salad dressing
directions: Melt sugar
and
butter
and add other ingredients, all but milk, into paste.
Add
milk last (or cream) and cook in a double boiler until thick.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Drain pimientos, reserving liquid. In medium saucepan over medium-high heat, cook onion and cumin in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in reserved pimiento liquid, broth, corn and parsley. Heat to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and cool slightly.
Cool can of Milnot and whip quite stiff.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Mix well with jello.
Fold this mixture into whipped Milnot.
Roll graham crackers fine and cream with butter and powdered sugar.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with 1 1/2 cups cracker mixture.
Top with other 1/2 cup.
Chill overnight.

title: manhattan vegetable saute
directions: Saute peppers, onions and garlic in margarine in same skillet until tender.
Stir tomatoes and basil; top with cheese.
Cover; continue cooking until cheese is melted.
Makes 2 servings.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook beef in a large skillet with butter until all pinkness is gone.
Add other ingredients except cheese, including noodles.
Put in a large dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pa'segtti
directions: Put it all together and stir it up faster and faster, then put it at the little table and put a big tractor in it, then eat it.

title: "blonde" oatmeal cookies(norwegian recipe)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add egg and melted butter. Put on cookie sheet with teaspoon (12 on each sheet).
Flatten them out with a spatula.
Bake at 350° until they are golden.

title: rat-ta-tat-toui(old english recipe)
directions: *Substitute 1/2 cup red cooking wine instead of oil and oregano, if desired.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour half of cake batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk and margarine over low heat.
Pour over baked cake. Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour the other half of cake batter over this and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: arroz relleno (ecuador)(rice with chicken filling)
directions: Boil chicken until well done.
Bone and chop meat.
Cook rice in broth with salt and olive oil until done.
Saute green pepper and onion until tender.
Add vegetables, tomato and olives.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add chicken and seasoning.
Mix well.
Cook for 2 minutes longer.
Place 2 slices of butter on bottom of 3-quart casserole.
Cover bottom with half the rice.
Add chicken mixture. Cover with remaining rice.
Place remaining slices of butter on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Garnish with eggs and parsley.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add powdered sugar (sifted) and peanut butter. Beat well. Gradually add milk. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm.

title: spanish style rice
directions: Combine tomato sauce, water, onion, green pepper, butter, salt, sugar, mustard and pepper in saucepan.
Cover and bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir with a fork.
Makes 3 1/2 cups or 4 servings.

title: zappable favorites apple crisp
directions: Place apples in an 8-inch microwave dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Melt butter in a small microwave bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Press down lightly.

Microwave on High for 8 minutes. Rotate dish 1/2 turn. Microwave another 6 to 8 minutes until apples are tender. Serve warm, cold, plain or with favorite topping. Other fruits may be used. May also use white instead of brown sugar.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough.
Spread in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: reese's cups
directions: Cream together margarine, 1 cup peanut butter and vanilla. Add sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Carefully blend in remaining cup of peanut butter.
Form into balls the size of a large marble.
Melt chocolate (and paraffin) in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate, using a toothpick to pick with.
Place on waxed paper. Yields 65 pieces.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and mix in soup, tuna and milk.
Put in lightly greased baking dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt stell's new mexican chili
directions: Cook all this until browned well, then simmer, covered, for 30 minutes for maximum tenderness.
Add water as needed so not to cook dry.

title: lazy stroganoff
directions: No need to brown the meat!
Use raw.

title: baked potato spears
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into wedges.
Brush with salad dressing.
Season with onion salt and pepper.
Place on greased 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 50 minutes, or until tender and golden.

title: leftovers pie
directions: In deep pie pan, mix meat, gravy, stuffing and vegetables. Top with potatoes and spread across pie to make a crust.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in cooking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk until well blended.
Pour in pan over butter.
Do
not stir.
Place fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Drain all the vegetables and mix together.
Mix half of each cheese with chicken.
In baking dish, put a layer of the vegetables, then a layer of chicken and some of the cheese. Repeat the layers.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes with butter.
Add sugars.
Beat egg yolks; add with cream, vanilla and spices until cool.
Stir in baking powder. Beat egg whites and fold in.
Fill 2 unbaked pastry shells.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then 350° for next 45 minutes.

title: green chili rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, saute onion in hot butter until golden.
Remove from heat and stir in hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf and salt and pepper.
Toss lightly to mix.
In a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 rice mixture, then half chilies and sprinkle 1/2 cheese. Repeat.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes until bubbly and hot. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Boil water, raisins and baking soda for 2 minutes. Set aside and let cool. Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs, salt, flour and nuts. Mix together with raisin mixture. Bake in 6 well-greased cans (cans are No. 2 size, like English peas, corn, etc.). Fill cans half full. Bake at 300° for 55 minutes.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients (applesauce, eggs, oleo, vanilla and brown sugar).
Add remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Mix yeast and sugar together.
Mix eggs, sugar, yeast mixture and shortening together.
Knead with flour, adding milk gradually. Let rise about 1 hour.
Knead down again.
Roll out into a circle.
Cut in triangles from center to edge.
Roll up.
Place on pans and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Check from time to time to see that bottoms aren't burning.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Place diced tomatoes, onion, celery and green pepper in bowl. In small bowl, combine sugar, water, vinegar and oil.
Mix well. Pour over vegetables.
Stir gently to mix.
Cover and chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Makes about 6 servings. Can add more vegetables to mixture as you desire.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, vanilla pudding, milk, pie spice, salt and 1/2 container Cool Whip together.
Put in a baked pie shell.
Put the rest of the Cool Whip on the top.
Chill.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In a skillet cook beef and onion with chili powder.
In saucepan heat together taco sauce, green chilies, enchilada sauce and soups.
Add meat mixture to this.
Break up tortilla chips and repeat layers of chips, meat mixture and cheese in a casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Place cheese on the top and cook for another 10 minutes.

title: chilled prawn curry
directions: Fry onion in pan over low heat until soft.
Add curry powder and cook 1 minute.
Add chicken stock, tomato puree, lemon juice and chutney.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Strain into a mixing bowl; leave to cool. Stir mayonnaise and cream into cooled curry sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add drained prawns and chill.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together all cake ingredients.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: hillbilly bean soup
directions: Wash the bean mixture.
Cover with water.
Add 1 tablespoon salt; soak for 3 hours or overnight.
Drain water.
Put beans in 2 quarts of fresh water.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook all day (at least 4 hours).
May be kept in covered container in refrigerator up to 4 days.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: In bowl, mix crushed wafers, butter, eggs, vanilla, nuts, coconut and sugar.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300°.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Cook all together the first 4 ingredients until hot. Add celery, onion and shrimp. Refrigerate for about 1 to 2 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini according to instructions.
Mix all ingredients. Let sit overnight.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Dissolve condensed milk in the cup of water.
Add sugar and butter.
Bring to a boil; add soda.
Test by firm drops from spoon; add vanilla.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Peel and chop apples.
Mix with pecans.
Pour in oil, well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter chip pineapple drops
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar.
Add vanilla and egg.
Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Blend into mixture. Stir in drained pineapple, peanut butter chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon into ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 370° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Cube bacon and fry.
Put bacon and fat in bowl.
Brown hamburger and onions together.
Put in bowl with bacon.
Add tomato soup and tomatoes.
Add spaghetti and mix thoroughly.
Put uncooked bacon slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or longer.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and sugar.
Save 1 cup of crumbs for top.
Then add the molasses, hot water and baking soda.
Mix together with the flour.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put topping on cake and put in oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter and add spices.
Pour over cereal and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake for 2 hours at 200°.
Stir about every 20 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop into ungreased muffin pans.
Makes 18 biscuits.

title: linda's lasagna
directions: Brown meat and add next 6 ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cook noodles.
Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan, 1/2 noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese mixture, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 meat. Repeat layers.
Bake at 370° for 30 minutes.
Let sit 15 minutes before cutting.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together; saving enough cheese and chips to sprinkle the top.
Cover and bake about 30 to 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: mexican beef and rice
directions: Brown beef and onions in large skillet, breaking beef into small pieces.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, olives, mushrooms and chili powder.
Bring to full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spicy chunk pickles
directions: Drain pickles and cut into chunks.
Combine sugar, vinegar and pickling spices.
Bring to a boil.
Pack pickles in jar.
Add vinegar mixture.
Cover.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: impossible mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in skillet until beef browns, then drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread beef mixture in pie plate. Sprinkle with chilies and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth and pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 to 35 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: easy, inexpensive salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix on high until blended well.
Store in refrigerator in glass jar.
Keeps well.
If it divides, shake jar.

title: sunny brunch eggs
directions: Add milk to Miracle Whip; add other ingredients.
Place cheese in casserole.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Blend in processor 30 seconds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over broccoli in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When almost done, top with crushed Cheez-Its crackers.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Blend soups and broth in bowl.
Layer 3/4 of the stuffing mix and chicken in 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (uncovered).
Yields 8 servings.

title: homemade hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together; store in airtight container. For one serving add 1/2 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: It takes 1/2 gallon persimmons to make 1 quart of pulp in colander.
Add a little water to persimmons, makes them easier to puree.
Mix ingredients, except margarine.
Melt it in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Put in freezer until ready to serve.
(Frozen crushed strawberries may be substituted for pineapple.)

title: chicken wing recipe
directions: Place chicken wings in gallon-size freezer bag (optional) and add remaining ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Occasionally turn bag over during marinating process.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh fruit.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: pink salad(serves 20)
directions: Mix milk with Cool Whip.
Carefully fold in the rest of the ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.
This is a big salad and can be frozen and sliced later if any is leftover.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese, whipped topping and peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Pour into pie crust and chill for several hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: christmas tree ornaments
directions: Blend salt and flour in bowl.
Add 1 cup water; knead dough until firm.
Roll dough out 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Use a nail to place a hole at top of ornament.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Varnish if desired.
You may add designs with a fork, etc.

title: peach crisp
directions: Combine rice, peaches and 1/3 cup sugar in buttered, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix flour, remaining sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in medium bowl; cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle flour mixture over rice and peaches.
Sprinkle walnuts over flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Put out 2 layers of crescent rolls on waxed paper to form large rectangle.
Roll with floured rolling pin until 15 x 15-inches.
Mix sausage with 2 beaten eggs.
Spread over rolls.
Sprinkle cheese and seasonings.
Start at one end and roll up jelly roll fashion tucking in edges as you roll.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush with beaten egg yolk.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Slice.
Freezes well.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into a dish to congeal, then spread sour cream on top.
Pour remaining mixture over this.
Congeal.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix butter and cheese together.
Add salt, pepper and flour.
Add cereal and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
May be served as an appetizer or snack.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Let Cool Whip soften.
Melt chocolate (keep aside one small block for garnish).
Mix 3/4 of the Cool Whip with chocolate until blended.
Spoon into pie crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Garnish with chocolate shavings.
Serve chilled.
